comments: Pam and Mark are  WONDERFUL. They are so accommodating and welcoming! Their home is beautiful, and the location cannot be any better. We wish we could have stayed longer for a hot breakfast with them, but unfortunately we had to make it a really quick trip. We can't wait to come back.
Ken was a great host. He went beyond our expectations to make our stay comfortable and fun. The suite was clean and lovely.

Convenient location for central Austin, really clean and great facility.  As mentioned by others wifi was not brilliant and views were into the courtyard which was a bit gloomy.  However Stacey was very helpful and the apartment is definitely a great base for Austin, with lots of space for everyone to relax.
Great stay, we loved the front porch in the early morning. Simple clean lines like a Zen retreat.
This place is one of the best AirBnB's I've stayed in. This was my second stay here. It was as good as the first stay. I look forward to the third stay.
Great cozy loft. I would stay there again happily.
The property is exactly what I expected. We had 5 people and all 5 had a place to sleep.  The place was comfortable and homelike. Perfect for a weekend away in austin.
Susan accepted my request quickly after my other cancelled on me. She was quick to respond to me and her place was so nice! We had a lovely time- very comfy beds!! Would definitely recommend!
Houston has a great place. Two nice cats and a great desk for doing work. I work from home during the day so having a desk was great!

The beds were so comfy and it was nice in there. Obviously not a 5-star hotel but wow, great place with a lot of useful stuff. Good location too but at first it didn't seem like it until you get your bearings. 

There's a book in the living room for a hide that helped me know where to go also! Great addition!
Lovely people & great accommodations. Pleasantly surprised with my first Airbnb experience. Will definitely come back.

The lovely, flexible and super friendly Amber made our stay perfect. The texas heat was hard on the head but the AC in suite spot made it easier to cope with. We received great tips from our host about places to eat, drink, swim and walk. We as guests felt extremely welcome and whenever we needed something we could ask without feeling intrusive. Really REALLY nice hosts! The room was clean and fully equipped and we couldn't wish for anything else. Thank you Amber!

This Austin Suite Spot is just as it sounds...extremely sweet!!!  The room is spacious, very clean, with a large closet, and an amazing bathroom!  The rainshower shower head is simply soothing and refreshing, and the large tub is perfect for a relaxing bubble bath!  The great room aside, the hosts are wonderful people who are helpful in any way possible.  I will definitely be looking to stay here again next time I am in Austin!

Amina was a great host, and we thoroughly enjoyed our stay.  For the most part, everything was exactly as described--excellent!

There were two things that surprised us that might be helpful to know.  First, the rental is fully attached to the home.  There is not a deadlocked door between the rental and rest of the home the way you might expect on a home apartment, just ordinary interior doors with push locks.  You also have to enter the main home (barely) in order to change the A/C.  This wasn't a deal breaker for us at all, but it did surprise us.  

Also, Amina was burning incense as we left each morning which filtered into our rental quite a bit.  This wasn't an issue because we were leaving each time, but with my husband's severe asthma, we may have had to ask her to not burn the incense if we were going to be in the house more.  I am sure she would have worked with us if it had been an issue.  So, if you have any respiratory issues like that, you may want to let her know ahead of time!

Again, these were two things that others might find helpful to know, but didn't take away from our experience.  Thank you Amina!
Bryan was an excellent friendly host. Couldn't have asked for a better experience. Located in a very quaint neighborhood.
My husband and I loved our stay here! They are stream is clean, and we love the outdoor shower! Location was perfect for us, we would definitely stay here again.

Gigi's guesthouse was lovely and we were very comfortable.
The neighborhood was quite nice too.
I would certainly stay here again.

Jennifer is talented. I love the Chinese element of art in the room. Dragon, phoenix,even the character  Âõç. That's the especial character used for wedding.;)) All in all, pretty good experience. Thanks for hosting us.
Amazing place, great people unusual, definitely recommend :) Thank you

This room is the perfect place for an adventurous couple to stay! The room was beautiful and clean with a comfortable bed and a luxurious shower. We really enjoyed being able to meet all of the animals on the property, which were super friendly. We were only able to stay for an evening, but we will definitely return on any future trips!
Matthew's place was very convenient to downtown. Cute cottage home with the essentials. I would stay there again.

Marianne's place is exactly as it looks in the pictures: bright, clean, and comfortable. We loved the art on the walls and the style of the whole house. She was extremely accommodating about check-in/out and was exceedingly responsive with communication. Some of my friends had never stayed with AirBnB before and now they say they definitely will in the future. Wonderful experience!
Shirin was a wonderful host!  Everything was immaculately clean and well-organized, this home is in a beautiful Austin neighborhood, and Shirin was gracious, kind and respectful.

Pete's apartment is just lovely. 

Three of us stayed for a week, there was plenty of room (plus room for one more), it is beautifully decorated and has everything that we needed. The code entry made it super easy to turn up and get in without having to worry about timings and late planes.

The apartment is in a great area, with great places to eat: Mothers, Julio's, Quacks and Hyde Park Bar and Grill are just 2 mins away as well as a fantastic local cheese shop (Antonelli's), a grocery store and a great juice bar all near by. There is also a bus stop just outside that takes 20mins to get downtown or 30 mins to South Austin.

When I go back to Austin this place will be top of my list.
This is a lovely apartment in a great area.  Very well appointed, comfortable and spacious.  The balcony is a great feature too.  And Hyde Park is a lovely, tree-lined, characterful area.

The place was everything we hoped for and more. Super clean, awesome layout, perfect neighbourhood with access to cute restaurants, cafes, and groceries, and great check-in/check-out organization. Thanks so much Pete, and keep up the awesome hospitality!

most comfortable bed ever. fantastic shower. incredible backyard. all things most important to us during our month road trip cross country. clean, spacious and right off highway which didn't bother us as it made getting into town a 7-10 min drive. wouldn't stay again!

We loved the tree house. It was really convenient that we could walk through the back yard and walk into the Magnolia Cafe. I think I gained about 5 pounds that weekend... We didn't expect awesome water pressure in the shower since it was a secondary building but was definitely surprised.
Perfect place for me and my friends whilst in Austin. Location right on top of 6th st, and the apartment was modern and comfortable. Could easily accommodate 7 in an open layout.

The host made the entire experience easy and gave us all the appropriate information on a timely manner. The location was the best part about this loft! We spent most of our time on the balcony enjoying the view and there were plenty of restaurants nearby so find some grub was never a problem. Lots of closet space and a big bathroom was a big plus for a group of girls! There were some uninvited guests that camped out by the street entrance of the loft that made a group of girls uneasy but there was a door guy that was there to clear the entrance. All and all we had one of the best experiences and staying at this loft made it that much better!!
Fantastic house! We had a great stay. Quiet neighborhood, with a couple bars sprinkled around close by. It really was the perfect location for our group. Safe, clean, modern.

Heidi was a great host. Her home is very spacious and comfortable, with lots of cute decorations. The location was perfect for me, quick and easy to access from I-35. South Congress isn't far, and there are plenty of shops and restaurants nearby. The bed was very comfortable, too. Heidi also was very quick to respond and took my reservation on very short notice.
Heidi was a great host and the apartment is great! Very clean, very spacious, very comfortable. She was extremely thorough with her instructions and we were always in contact with her. 10/10.
The bed is so comfortable!!!!!!!!!! The place is amazing.... the shower is roomy and comfortable.......
The house is in a great location, close to all South Congress has to offer, and not a far ride from downtown.  Coordination with the host was easy and the place was very welcoming and clean.

cute space well-outfitted with all the necessities in a great location in central austin; jason was super responsive through the whole process from the first message i sent. would definitely recommend this spot for a single traveler or couple wanting to make a great little austin neighborhood their home for a few days!
Andrew and Laura were very welcoming and great hosts.  Great location, centrally located and within walking distance from a lot of great restaurants and bars.  Would highly recommend!
Perfect spot right off South Congress.  Close to many restaurants, bars, and shops. Very nice place.  It is so much nicer than the pictures.  Really enjoyed it.
Wonderful host! Had a minor hiccup with my car while there and Suzy offered to help me if I needed. Very much appreciate her  generosity.

Had a terrific time, the place was clean, perfect location, easy to find and get into, never heard a word from our neighbors (in a good way) and it had everything we needed. Would definitely stay here again next trip to Austin.  Thanks !
Dealing with Stephanie was so easy and nothing but a pleasure. The place was spotless and very charming; we loved it! We will definitely be back :)

Our stay at Steven's ranch felt grand. The home is large and beautifully furnished. The outdoor animals were friendly and the neighbor, Bill, was kind and helpful upon our arrival. Additionally, we found 2 great restaurants down the road which stayed open late, one Mexican and the other Vietnamese. We felt very comfortable in Steven's home and hope to visit again.

Charlie's place was great! it had more than enough room for the four of us to stay.  The house was very clean and I wouldn't give it a second thought about staying again. 

The location was perfect for us. everything we wanted to go was only a short little drive.

Also, it was pretty nice having some records around to have some music going. pretty good selection, i might add. 

Overall, I would definitely love to stay here again next time I decide to head to Austin.
This was an awesome stay. It was my first time in Austin and I got a great feel of what it's like to be a local.

The apartment complex was very nice. Offer responded quickly to our last minute inquiry and was very welcoming and hospitable. The room and apartment in general were extremely clean and comfortable. The bed and sheets were comfortable and clean. It was an overall great experience.

Offer was very nice and provided a nice clean room with a desk and wifi that worked very well and a clean bathroom.  The bed was comfortable and I slept very well.  The neighborhood was very nice and very conveniently near to my work.  I enjoy talking to Offer and look forward to staying there again sometime when it is available again.
Great condo in a convenient location walkable to downtown Austin. Spacious with all the amenities you would expect, very clean, comfortable beds, well equipped kitchen.

Brittany was great to communicate with and her house was fantastic! It was quiet, clean, very very comfortable and we couldn't ask for a better place to stay  for the weekend! I would recommend her place to anyone and we sure hope to be back again next year!
Ok place. Lauren was helpful and communicative. Bathroom was a mess.
Great space.   Great location.  Great host.   Lost count regarding how many times I have stayed here.

Ward was a great host aswell as his house. Everything was layed out for us house was real clean and nice real quiet neighborhood and stores are close by aswell downtown was only 10 minutes away. We had a great time and would stay at Ward's house again on our next trip to Austin!
Nice area and centrally located to most things. Only stayed 1 night but enjoyed it.
Though we never got to meet Mary, she was very quick with replying to our messages prior to and during our stay. The room was as described and we enjoyed our stay.

Wonderful host! So helpful during our stay. Really recommend Paulines place!
Loved the room and area aswell.

I really enjoyed my stay at Pauline's.  Her house is in a convenient location, close to the bus stop that goes right down South Congress, which was important to me since I didn't rent a car. (the HEB grocery store sells weekly bus passes)  I do wish I had  spent more time around the the St. Edwards University area , which is right down the street from the house.  Pauline was very helpful with her suggestions around town.   I enjoyed my conversations with her  after a long day in Austin.  I'll definitely stay here next time I'm in Austin.
Very nice place close to lots of authentic Austin bars and restaurants and within 10 minute drive of everything you would want to do in Austin.

Summary: beautiful, close to SoCo/6th st/Downtown and UT, very safe and private, full amenities, brilliant host.

The photos of the casita are beautiful, but actually being in the space and staying there was divine. As I explored the place and all it's charms and thoughtfulness laid out by our host Dolina, I was more excited to stay here in the Casita than to explore the city the evening I arrived. Hunger eventually drove me out and I was within a short 5 minute or less drive to Downtown/6th street, Zilker Park, a mile from the heart of SoCo. UT was about a 10-15 minute drive. I could not image a better location, close enough to everything I wanted to visit, but not waking up to people trampling across the sidewalks of the casita like some places. I would definitely recommend the Casita to friends and family. I even started to feel guilty for not bring an extra friend to share the experience with us. 

Extras: comfy bed, fluffy pillows, thoughtful treats of chocolate, tangerines, coffee, cream, and tea. Also a glorious collection of books to read and plenty of space to sprawl out and enjoy them. After confirming with Dolina, I was able to have a very flexible check out time.

What can I say about this place, other than it's PERFECT in every way. I really enjoyed my stay there. Dolina was extremely friendly and accommodating in every way. She went out of her way to give me a 5 star experience at the birdhouse. If there was a class to be taught on "how to host on airbnb", she'd be first on my list to teach it. The place was quiet, well-appointed and full of books that I would actually read. And the bus stop was just around the corner that took me straight downtown in about 10 minutes. Very convenient. I wish I could take this place back with me to San Francisco!
Amazing house and even better couple... Very nice people...Had resources and snacks set up when we arrived and gave us a great tour of the home, and made us feel welcome and comfortable...
Easy check in. Beautiful house.

This is the second year in a row that my team has stayed at Chloe's listing for SXSW Interactive.  She is a fantastic host, the house is clean and nicely furnished.  The backyard was recently renovated, and it is amazing, a perfect place to host small events, and just hang out.  If your party is interested, she will give you some great local places to hang out, grab a meal, or a beer.  We are from the Bay Area, and she pointed us to a sports bar that let us watch the Warriors.  I really can't say enough about how positive the experience is staying here.  The big bonus is onsite washer and dryer.  I love being able to come home with clean clothing!!!  She always checks in the morning of arrival and departure to make sure everything is good.

The house looked exactly like the listing on the site. Very clean, and spacious enough to accommodate me and the group of 5 I came with. Host let us enjoy ourselves as much as we wanted, as well as communicated her concerns to make sure everything was smooth. We had a great time at SXSW and especially at the home! Can't wait to visit Austin again.

Would definitely recommend that others stay at Chloe's place! We had some challenges with evenly heating the house (it was 20 degrees through part of the weekend) but overall everything was great! The house was well-kept and had all the essentials. And plenty of parking.

Awesome place! Walkable to the heart of east Austin. Uber is always around if you need to go downtown or the campus area. The backyard is great place to chill at the end of the day. they email you with all the necessary instructions. Very cool folks! I'd go back.
Such a lovely place! We had the best time. Looking forward to our next stay here.

Dani was incredibly responsive with everything we needed and very pleasant in the process.  Everything was as we expected it and more.  The house was very cozy and had a great Austin feel to it, also didn't hurt that it was a 3 minute walk to Torchey's Taco's ;)  Would recommend this to couple or set of couples looking to explore South Congress and a quick bike ride/cab form downtown and 6th street.

Brooke's place is located walking distance from Barton Springs and downtown Austin. There are tons of cute bars and restaurants nearby. We fit 5 people comfortably in the apartment. It was cozy, clean, and more spacious than I imagined. I would definitely recommend staying here!

Cristin and Olya are really kind, cool and intelligent people. I had great conversations with them, and it was really fun to hang out with them and share food and a few beers. The house is in a great area, with lots of trees, and close to some really iconic Austin cafes.

Brand and Anni were awesome! We got to the house a little early to drop off our stuff and they welcomed us with open arms and made us feel right at home! The house is just as advertised.  Great location in East Austin, only a quick drive/ uber ride away from downtown.  Definitely recommend!
D'Ann was a great host. She met us at arrival and offered welcome drinks. Have a house tour and provided a wealth of information about the area.
Great location and a beautiful place. Ashley was super helpful with pre-arrival accommodations, and the house was very well prepared upon arrival. Excellent place for any large group going to Austin.
Ashley was an excellent host and we loved staying at Casa Roja!  Everything was just as beautiful as the pictures!

This home was exactly as listed, no surprises.  It was very clean, comfortable and had everything we needed to have a great stay. The location of the house was great. Easy access to all the places we wanted to go.
had a great stay with Brooke. I am a regular Airbnb user but first time at this property. Really enjoyed place and assistance.
Had a great time here, unit was super clean with all the amenities you would expect from a luxury hotel.  The owner was very accommodating and would highly recommend staying at any of her properties.

Brooke was prompt and thorough with helpful information on finding, parking, checking in, staying at, and exploring around the Little Josephine property. My wife, 2 kids (11 & 15), and I were very comfortable and spent much of our 4 days lounging around with books, movies, and board games! We found ample dining and shopping opportunities near by. This charming location was the PERFECT getaway!

We had the most perfect stay in Adam's studio while visiting Austin for  the iheartcountry festival.  The studio was clean and spacious and the reviews do not lie---the bed is AMAZING.  Just a short walk to South Congress and $5-$10 Uber/Lyft ride to all other hot spots. We didn't want to leave and would stay here again in a heartbeat when visiting Austin! Couldn't have asked for a better first time airbnb experience!
It was awesome. Everything was clean, roomy, comfortable. Enrique was a great host who was fast to answer any questions.
Very nice place! Highly recommend you stay here. Host is quiet, friendly, communicative and provides everything as listed. 10/10 would book again.

We enjoyed our stay at Brooke's cottage. It was exactly as the pics show.... very clean and nicely furnished. Loved the location and close to park area. Would certainly recommend and stay there again!
Charles was a great host! His place is the perfect location, right off South Congress. Thanks for a great stay.

We stayed in Charles' condo over a long weekend. It was a great location, minutes from South Congress, just as described. We used Lyft and Uber to get many places and it was very affordable with how close the condo is to everything. The condo itself was very clean and comfortable. Charles was a great host. Weeks before our trip he offered to have our favorite drink waiting in the condo and also provided us with advice on many things to do. His advice list was great and we referenced it the entire stay. We would definitely stay here again! Many thanks to Charles for a great Airbnb experience.
The apartment was in a good location and suited our needs just fine.  Street traffic is a bit noisy, just fyi.

Great getaway place.  Had everything we needed and more.  Loved that we could walk to everything we wanted to visit in soco.  The neighborhood is lovely.  Bed was comfy and just felt like home. Hope to stay again!

Charles place was perfect to crash during a hetic business trip. The bed was super comfortable! Internet was really slow, but he mentioned he was working on getting it fixed! A 15 minute walk from some good stuff on South Congress, I walked to dinner a few times.

Jon sent us a great welcome package before we arrived, so we felt very prepared prior to the trip. The studio was perfect for a long weekend exploring Austin and was very central to everything we wanted to do. The studio was very clean and the pullout sofa was pretty comfortable!
This was a great apartment for 6 girls.  There was plenty of room and it was conveniently located. It was very clean as well.  I would definitely come back and stay here again.
Lauren's condo was perfect for our stay! It couldn't be in a better location in downtown Austin and she was responsive to any questions that we had. Everything was very clean and as depicted!

Great house in an excellent new estate. 7 of us stayed there for SXSW and to do lots of things around Austin for the week. There was more than enough room and the house was immaculate when we arrived, with a large living room and dining area and a very nice outdoor area for when the weather is good. In order to get downtown we took the bus which runs every 20 minutes and is about a 5 minute walk - perfect if you don't want to drive and cant park during SXSW. Its also pretty near the I35 which made is easy to get north or south of the city to do things in the surrounding area. All in all a great place to stay.

Carlos's place was fantastic to stay at! It really felt like a checking into a hotel in many ways because he laid out recommendations of where to go and what to do, had fresh towels and toiletries out in the bathroom, and obviously went out of his way to leave the place absolutely spotless for my stay. It felt like I was renting from a true professional who is also very thoughtful. The space had everything I could need including a comfortable bed and lots of room in a modern apartment in the heart of the college district. Getting in and out was a breeze including check-in and check-out, and Carlos is an exceptional communicator. He was always only a phone call or text away and was also a very appreciative host. Excellent experience, would stay here again when visiting Austin.

Great, clean place in a fun area.  I felt I got a great dose of the hip-Austin experience. Carlos is super nice and accommodating, and is very easy to communicate with.  Really helped facilitate a great trip!

Sweet accommodating host. The home and room was super clean, with cute decor everywhere! Host offered great recommendations and location was spectacular and super convenient. I would definitely stay on rainey street again!

Nicky was so welcoming and sweet. She made us feel so comfortable. I would absolutely visit her again! She was clean, hospitable, and I felt very safe with her. She went out of her way to pick us up, she always had a smile. She is a great person.
This loft is a really beautiful place to stay.  Great amenities and very comfortable.  Nice patio and nice backyard.
Great stay here - condo was clean & comfortable and neighbors were friendly.  Short walk to Congress and easy to get to other parts of town via Lyft.  Would recommend to friends!

This home is amazing and eclectic and a very "Austin" place to stay. We really enjoyed it! The host was great, very informative and easy going. The host wasn't there during our stay but was still very available to us which I appreciated. I would definitely recommend this place!
Great place and location! Great value!

Michele was great - loved the house!  It was quite charming with lots of fun, whimsical touches. Bedroom was perfect. "Treat", her cat was adorable, and I wanted to take her home. I was able to use the kitchen freely which was so nice, and Michele's china was lovely.  Had great conversations after returning from the wedding I attended Sunday.  

The neighborhood was perfect. Houses were interesting, had great landscaping and we were close to everything.   I look forward to returning in the future. Thank you for your sense of humor and your gracious hospitality.

Jerome
Delightful space in a fabulous location!!!!
Nice farm

Jess was very responsive and truly wanted us to be comfortable and have all the information necessary for a wonderful stay.  The cottage is cozy, with plenty of space.  Particularly nice to  have the washer and dryer on site.  The bed and pillows were also very nice.  The bathroom is small, but has everything you need.  We have family close to there, and enjoyed walking to restaurants and just around the interesting transitioning neighborhood; full of character!

Fantastic place and experience. Stayed for a business trip. Was super clean, and quiet at night. Ted met us out front upon arrival. Location was great for walking and riding bike share b-cycles everywhere! Highly recommend.
The house is in a great neighborhood. The house has the modern amenities. The heated pool was amazing

This house is AWESOME. Very spacious, modern, and accommodating. I stayed there with 3 other people and had plenty of room. It's perfect for having company over before heading out downtown. Would definitely recommend!

We stayed for 2 full weeks. The house is very nice, it is really as shown in the pictures. The host was available by email and by phone at all times. We enjoyed our stay, certainly this house will be our fist option to stay next time we travel to Austin.
Wonderful trip. House was clean and comfortable. Great location Definitely recommend this house.

Perfect spot to settle in for a week long business trip. Walking distance to plenty of food choices. I stayed alone (female) and felt so safe at the apt and walking around the neighborhood at night. Wifi was fast and dependable to get work done. Tracy supplied plenty of coffee, too!

The house was lovely in an up-and-coming neighborhood.  Easy 20 minute walk to 6th street, or cheap cab ride into town, so a rental car isn't necessary.  Space is open with good light, and backyard is huge.  The kitchen has incredibly nice and new amenities, and except a dishwasher it has everything else you could need. Overall very good experience, would rent here again if we came to Austin in the future.

Our stay at the Eastside House was perfect. The house had everything we needed to enjoy a great Austin weekend! Jessica was super accommodating, friendly, and very available during our trip. The house location was ideal for biking and walking around town. We rented bikes in the neighborhood and made our way down to Lady Bird Lake for paddleboarding and lunch on Rainey street. It was a great stay overall!
Awesome place! Great communication with owner and an all around great experience.
Great location with plenty of room for 6! Jessica was very responsive & kind.

John was very welcoming to us for our trip, providing water, a nice room, TV and wifi. John helped give us the lay of the land in what areas would have the most traffic and helped provide us with a care free experience in Austin.

We had an awesome time during our stay here!  It's a clean and comfortable place with pretty much everything you'd need.  Knowing nothing at all about Austin before our visit, we appreciated having Lanis show us around the city and bring us to some interesting spots.  Sara, Amanda and Lanis are definitely fun and friendly company, making us feel at home.  Good times!
Stayed here the night before meeting friends for ACL. Great, safe location, would definitely stay again!
Great little spot for my business travels.  Awesome value.  Will stay there again for next business travel.

The instructions provided by Caleb made his place easy to find and navigate through. The bed was super comfortable and the Netflix was perfect to end my day each night! Plenty of room in the fridge to store the food I had brought for my stay. About a 20 minute drive from where I was visiting (45th and Lamar). Made a convenient stop by the Aboretum on my way into town as well.

Mike was great with communicating throughout check in/out and got back to us with great suggestions for music venues when we reached out the first evening. Really enjoyed seeing this part of the city and having a comfortable spot to return to & relax/make a meal at the end of the day. The airstream was tidy and cozy but not at all cramped- would recommend for anyone looking to have a mellow visit with access to the downtown area!

Hilary is incredibly nice and welcoming. As long as you don't mind being off the frontage road of a highway it is a good location. You can get anywhere with the highway. I prefer to walk which was not easy to do from there. The space is a little cramped, and I found the futon to be not very comfortable, but I'm used to a super soft bed and you can feel the bars on the futon. You don't really get your own space much, and if you like privacy there really isn't any, except that Hilary is not there much. You do have access to her kitchen and even her laundry which is nice.

The cielo room was absolutely wonderful. The location was great - close to downtown by foot and car. The neighborhood is adorable and being renovated all around. Great food and nightlife options nearby, but also close enough to walk downtown or take a few minutes drive to see more of the city. Ginger was more than accommodating, and what you've read is right - her dog is the sweetest! I would completely recommend Ginger's place to anyone heading to the Austin area!

The room was great! Cozy, clean, nicely decorated, and enough space for the two of us. The location is perfect to walk to a few close coffee shops or restaurants or bike to just about anywhere else. We parked our car right downstairs. Everything went smoothly and am looking forward to renting it again!

I stayed at Casa Alta Vista for one night and wish I could have stayed longer! Tim & Tamara's  lovely guest space is very charming, clean, private and only 5 minutes to downtown. Fantastic location and neighborhood. The bed was large and comfy....I slept like a rock. The bathroom is updated with very nice quality tile and finishes. The shower was my best friend the morning after a long night out! It was the perfect place for my overnight stay in Austin. I hope to be back soon and stay longer next time!

We had a wonderful stay at Tim and Tamara's home! The bedroom and sitting area were extremely spacious and attractive. The king-size bed was comfortable and the room was quiet. There was a daybed, mini fridge, microwave, and Keurig coffee maker in the sitting room. Our hosts provided the coffee, and there were dishes and silverware available in the cupboard. The bathroom was beautifully decorated with tile floor and shower, and the towels were luxuriously thick! We loved the neighborhood as well. It was easy access from Interstate 35 and close to the river and South Congress, but still had a secluded feel with tree-lined streets and beautiful homes. We had a chance to meet Tamara and their younger daughter; both were delightful to talk to. We could not have chosen a better place to stay in Austin!!

My fianc√© and I love our time at Tim's and Tamara's place in Austin.  It was a breeze to find, centrally located to everything we wanted to see, and lovely.  The use of the door code made it really easy to check in and out.  The apartment itself has a really comfortable, big bed and all sorts of amenities.  The coffee and snacks that were provided were also a nice touch.  We'll definitely be asking to stay here again on our next trip to Austin!

What a lovely stay! Tim and Tamara's Air BnB is the nicest I've ever seen. They sent me great directions well before the visit, and we're wonderful with communication overall. They stocked the room with pretzels, chocolate, water, coffee, shampoo, conditioner, soap, and extra toiletries. The place was extremely clean, and the couch and bed were quite comfortable. I'd definitely stay again the next time I'm in Austin. The location can't be beat. 15 min walk to downtown and South Congress.

Jeremy was great. Super communicative and fast to respond to any and all questions. The house was very clean and cute. Jeremy also left my group a nice goodie package to help us enjoy the space and feel super welcome.
Jeremy was in constant communication with us the entire stay and leading up to it. We felt very well taken care of and the place was great!

Ryan's place was perfect!  Great location and very clean.  It could be a bit loud from time to time when neighbors were coming home late night, but the location, cleanliness and overall great hosting were wonderful.  We would definitely stay here again!

This is a great funky house, with lots of interesting decks and quiet nooks for reading.  It is in a quiet wooded neighborhood, perfect for a stay-cation away.  There is lots of deck and patio space for outdoor grilling and entertaining, and there are two chimineas for an evening campfire.  The location offers a close walk to Zilker park or to lots of great restaurants, food trucks, and Uncle Billy's brew and BBQ on Barton Springs, or a short drive to downtown destinations or South Congress.
The hosts were very helpful and always there when we needed anything.  They  made us feel welcome since the very beginning of our stay.

Overall, I loved my time at Jason's place. The unit was clean, charming, and perfectly situated in the lovely Clarksville neighborhood. I would definitely stay here again - in fact, I am. Next week! Can't wait!
I had a nice stay in Jason's place. Very clean. Easy to walk to downtown. Checking in and out was super easy. Thanks so much!
Comfy bed, convenient location, easy communication. I would stay here again.
We had a great stay! Excellent hospitality and the room was quite comfortable! Definitely would love to come back!

Jaime and Mike were wonderful hosts, we felt very welcome and the guest house is very nice and cozy. They've thought of everything when it comes to stocking the space with necessities; we felt as if we could have practically forgotten to pack luggage at all and been able to get by with no trouble! The location is nice and quiet, but still manages to make many of Austin's attractions easily accessible. This listing was part of what made our weekend in Austin so enjoyable!

This was the PERFECT AirBNB Experience! The location is perfect and the guest house is exactly what we were looking for. Located in a great neighborhood , walking distance to an amazing coffee shop (Patika) , I highly recommend staying here. Jamie and her husband are super friendly and I got to meet their three adopted doggies which were also super cute. The guest house is stocked with information about Austin, all the amenities one would need & then some. I was so happy. The AC works great, which was a nice treat after being out in the Texas sun. Snacks and drinks & bathroom amenities were the cherry on top. This was one of my best AirBNB experiences ever, if not best. Love love love.

Mary's little yellow cottage was an ideal spot to start our vacation. My wife, her mum, and I landed in Austin late in the evening but when the taxi delivered us to Mary's place, we instantly felt at home in her clean!, tidy house. The beds were comfortable, linens fresh and high quality, and the kitchen had everything Teri needed to cook up a Texas storm. We were hungry when we arrived and didn't realize the 24-hour HEB grocery was so close so we scooted across the street and met the excellent Javier at El Tacorrido. He and his coworker - we didn't catch her name - fixed us up with tasty Mexican food and Texan hospitality. They stayed open a few minutes later just to serve us, their last customers of the day. We had a great night's sleep and awoke the next morning, eager to investigate Austin. As we'd decided to pick up a car when leaving we were thrilled with the terrific bus service available 100 feet from Mary's door. We bought $2 all-day ride passes, an excellent value, and spent our time in Austin checking out the Capitol, the Blanton Museum, the O. Henry House, the funky shops and booteries on South Congress, Whole Foods' flagship store, the quirky G'raj Mahal (delicious Indian food), and the Austin City Limits Theater to see the Gipsy Kings. On our last morning in Austin, Teri and I walked downtown in less than an hour to the Hertz location on E. 10th and were very happy to meet Tim, who fixed us up with a nice rental car at a great rate. The people we met during our time in Austin were friendly and helpful to a person, no matter how casual our encounter. Austin is a wonderful town full of interesting, welcoming folks such as Mary, our Airbnb hostess. Mary was quick and clear in all our communication and renting her place got our vacation off on the right foot. I can't say enough good things. Thanks very much, Mary! We look forward to staying with you again some time.

Stu & Teri and Pat
Mary and her cottage were both fantastic. A well-equipped kitchen and goodies in the fridge made us feel right at home. Mary rocks and this spot is a wonderful way to spend time in Austin.

I stayed there a week and the place was great; lots of beautiful patio space to roam, do yoga...etc. Perfect location if you love the greater outdoors as its right next to trails, outdoor swimming etc. Just gorgeous. Plus close to downtown, maybe ten bucks tops for a cab.

The hosts were very accomodating, just really sweet. We did yoga together an 1they also set up a reservation at a nice place on a budget. i had a great time. 

The bedroom is under a loft but there's a lot of light, and curtains for privacy.  Tons of storage! there are two twin beds above the loft so a group of friends who want to stick together could rent out the whole room, easy - share the bathroom and have a back entrance patio without disturbing anyone- which i would highly recommend. Good price too.

 It could be possibly ackward with the bathroom door lock being none existent but i didnt have a problem as a girl and the other one did have one. The place has everything you need, I even saw ear plugs on the table lol. I will definately keep in touch. Met really great people to network with in the future. Five Stars!
Super chill, comfortable, you def get what you expect, a nice clean safe place to rest up.

Brett was very accommodating and flexible when it came to our arrival time and made it as easy as possible for us to get settled in. The house was clean and had everything he promised. I would definitely recommend Brett and this listing to my friends.

Our stay here was just right! Great location. The backyard is gorgeous and tranquil and the room is spacious. Although the whole studio is only one room and there is no proper wall between the bedroom and bathroom, the bathroom still feels private enough. Stayed here during ACL and the studio just made the experience perfect.

Our 1 night stay was perfect. Everything we needed had been considered and was waiting for us. The beds were comfortable, and there was coffee. Our kind hosts felt accessible and at the same time mindful of our privacy. We look forward to staying with them again.
Great location for enjoying downtown Austin!  Cozy, fun place to relax!

Absolutely love this space - it's beautiful, comfortable, private, surrounded by nature, and so convenient to anywhere you want to get in Austin. Elizabeth is an organized, gracious, considerate hostess who instantly made me feel comfortable in her space, yet at the same time fully respected my privacy (the space is separate from the main house, but if I had questions about anything she was just a text away!) Will definitely stay here again the next time I'm in Austin!

This place was perfect! Excellent location, clean and comfy space, amazing breakfast. It was very private, with your own key and separate entrance. I recommend taking a walk to the Austin Brewing Company beer garden when you arrive, so you can stroll through their cute neighborhood and enjoy some great beer.  And Jessie and Kevin are awesome hosts; we can't wait to go back!
Pixie was a lovely host. His accommodations were clean and comfortable and I enjoyed leafing through his cookbooks. I felt right at home for my 3 night stay. His other rave reviews are spot on!
This is what airbnb should feel like... A friend hosting you for a few days. Lovely home,  well located, and a great host. Thanks for having me!

ok wow you want a place to that has it all stay here - host was awesome - we didnt have anything to drink and one of our guest lost his luggage - i didnt see the note the owner left that basically said we could use anything in the house including toiletries and the BAR - great location nice place and very very quite - would recommend to anyone - thanks again
The host canceled this reservation 38 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.

My boyfriend and I stayed at this condo and loved it! Very clean and modern with a nice-sized bathroom and kitchen. Perfect for 1-2 people. It is in a quiet neighborhood close to the Capitol and a 15-20 minute walk from the fun parts of 6th St. I highly recommend this place!

This downtown Austin condo is the perfect home base to explore all of the great things that Austin has to offer. Situated in a quiet neighborhood, the studio style apartment is impeccably clean, comfortable, and has many of the basics that you may need while on the road.

 As a first time visitor to Austin, the apartment provided me the opportunity to live and experience the city like a local, but also provided me with easy access to popular spots in downtown and SoCo. It‚Äôs only a quick 15 minute walk to 6th street, and an easy bike or car trip to great restaurants in Hyde Park and East Austin. 

While I didn't meet Kristi, she was a wonderful host and was proactive in her communications. She was always quick to respond to any questions, and the check-in/out process was seamless. 

I highly recommend this location if you're looking for a quiet respite from the busy downtown and touristy areas of the city, but want easy access to nightlife and great food.  I would gladly stay in Kristi‚Äôs apartment again.

Nice clean place good for a short stay in Austin.  Perfect location in between the U of Texas and Downtown. The A/C was a huge plus, in the Texas heat.  Cable TV is listed as an amenity but it was the most basic of cable only offering local TV and community access.   So if you want to catch the game on ESPN its not an option.   Other wise the place is great.
Host was great I flew in on a red eye and didnt have my room access code but she called me back at like 600am to help me with access. Total life saver! Ill be back next year for sure!
Very nice, clean, and convenient! I will absolutely stay here again and recommend to others. A++

Great location and house.  Close to 6th Street and Downtown.  Hosts were friendly, very helpful, and had little treats for us when we arrived.  Very clean, welcoming, efficient house.  Hope to stay again next trip to Austin!

Awesome little house in a great Austin neighborhood. It was clean, well stocked, efficiently laid out. Anna and Chad are easy going. We didn't arrive until 1 a.m but check-in, check-out, and communication were all seamless. Anna let us leave our bags and explore the city after we checked out. She even lent us an umbrella since we came unprepared. Would (and plan to) book again.
Robert was quite accommodating as we strolled into town last minute! His place is awesome and conveniently located to everywhere in Austin we planned on going! Would definitely stay again.

Awesome stay. I have a pretty picky girlfriend that had nothing negative to say! We were both worried being allergic to animals, but Leia and Keri were excellent. Their home is an extremely clean and comfortable place that's hosted by helpful and friendly people. If you're allergic to animals I wouldn't let it stop you from staying in this great home! It's located in quiet, gorgeous neighborhood that's about a $26 cab ride from downtown. We didn't get to meet Keri, but Leia was friendly and made sure we had everything we needed. We had a great time!

Leia & Keri were very welcoming and have such a beautiful home. The upstairs oasis was nothing less than amazing. They were very helpful on accommodating to all of our needs and telling us about all the fun things to do in Austin. The whole upstairs area was very private and definitely worth the money. You will not be getting a better stay in Austin. Their home was about 15 minutes away from Downtown Austin and pretty close to everything else. We will definitely be staying here again the next we're in Austin.
Leia and Keri were fantastic hosts! They have a beautiful home and we're very accommodating. The room was very clean and the location was great.

My girlfriend and I stayed in Paul's Airstream for a weekend of cycling in the hills of Austin and it was the perfect place. The location is hard to beat and close to both downtown and the Westlake hills and the Airstream is both unique and  comfortable. When we arrived we found everything ready for us, even some orange juice, croissants and beer. Of course the best thing after a long ride is a hot shower and on the way to it Paul might invite you for some beer or coffee in his kitchen. He and his family are great hosts and made us feel at home during our (too short) stay.

The stay at Sharon's house was super! Great cosy house, clean bathroom and comfy bedroom. She had bought some Bagels and cream cheese for breakfast :-) really felt like home...

Thanks so much again.

Kim is a awesome host. She is super friendly and we felt at home in her space. She gave us hoola hoop lessons (totally fun) and great tips on ATX eats. Check out Seventh Flag coffee down near her place and ask her to tell you the story of her family and the building.

Kim was an excellent host! She was very warm and welcoming and made us feel totally comfortable in her beautiful space. I thought she went above and beyond to ensure we had a pleasant stay. She provided a ton of information about the house prior to our arrival and also had a guidebook with restaurant recommendations. 

My friend and I stayed in the Austin History Room. The room was clean, and Kim even set up an extra bed for us so that we didn't have to share. The massage chair upstairs is amazing.

The location was great - walking distance from a ton of good restaurants. We stayed with Kim for Austin City Limits and walked to and from the festival each day. 

Would definitely stay with Kim again and would recommend to anyone looking to visit Austin!

My husband and I loved staying at Gracie's. This is definitely a hidden gem. It was our first time using AirBnB and the experience was amazing. 

Gracie, Teo and their adorable cat Gustavo were the best hosts and made us feel at home. Unfortunately, we didn't get to spend a lot of time them due to their schedule and our schedule, however; they were so sweet to stay up and welcome us on our first night, even though they had to wake up early for work the next morning and were helpful about answering any questions we had and leaving us plenty of information about the area.  

It takes a couple of minutes to drive to everything (1st Street, Lamar, Congress and Downtown), you can even bike to a lot of places too and they even let you use their bikes. It also provides easy access to Highways and Freeways which was important to us since we were headed to San Antonio and Fredericksburg on different days. 

We would definitely recommend staying at Gracie's and we will definitely stay at her place when we visit Austin again next year.
Gracie and Teo, thank you for hosting! This was my first experience with Airbnb and you accommodations were just as expected.

My stay with Gracie and Teo was great! They went above and beyond to make my stay with them wonderful. The room that I stayed in was clean, super stylish, and comfortable. They also recommended where to eat and visit. The location was perfect as it didn't take long to get downtown and public transportation and uber were not expensive at all. I was able to hang out with both of them after my day adventures and I loved speaking with Gracie. She is so vibrant, warm, and just a lovely person all around. We clicked instantly and it was like hanging out with an old friend. On the day that I was leaving Teo made me an amazing latte (he even went to buy whole milk to make me one since they only had almond milk, and I'm allergic to almonds--super nice!), we all went out to breakfast together, shopped a bit, and they dropped me off at the airport. They didn't have to do any of that. I'm so grateful to have met such genuine, positive, loving, warm people. When I go back to Austin I will definitely be staying with them!

This really was a perfect place to stay. It's very cozy and relaxing and in a quiet neighborhood with an easy drive of downtown. The place was thoughtfully filled with nice touches: keyless entry, chocolates by the bedside, a delicious chocolate chip cookie, water, soda, wine, snack bars, and both regular and decaf coffee. I also forgot to pack sunscreen, bug spray, and deodorant so I was ecstatic to find Jay and Jayne also provided these (and more) in the bathroom (and the deodorant is the spray kind, also a thoughtful touch). I would stay here again in a heartbeat. One of the most well-executed Airbnb's I've stayed in with a thoughtfulness that would rival most hotels.

We had an amazing time at Club Ed. It was such a nice place. There were some problems and Ed was always on top of it. If you're visiting Austin and need a place to stay, it doesn't get any nicer than this for the price.
We absolutely loved our stay at Eloisa's. Such a beautiful, modern, clean home and comfortable room. The location was great, close to everything. Would definitely stay here again next time.

I can't say enough good things about Kim and her place. Our room was spacious and the bed was really comfortable. The apartment is really cute with a great shower and access to a washer/dryer and amazing air conditioning. The location is fantastic, a short drive or Uber from everything we wanted to do, with great places to eat just a short walk away. The apartment complex has a pretty courtyard and pool to use as well. Kim was the best! Super friendly and really helpful with tons of advice on what to do and where to go. Her dog was SO SWEET and the best to hang around. We had a great time!! Highly recommend.
This was my first time using airbnb and I'm never going back. I loved the house and the location.

What a great place to stay in downtown Austin! Alexis was a wonderful host and had everything prepared for the 3 of us during our stay, including welcome snacks and beers! She also was available at any time if we had any queries. I would highly recommend for anyone wanting to stay near the city!

Downtown Oasis 2 was a fantastic place to stay on my work trip to Austin. Alexis made everything very easy, and was readily available for any questions or needs I might have. The apartment is exactly as pictured...neat, clean and cozy with everything you need including a phone charger on the bedside shelf! It is in a nice friendly neighborhood and  a short walk from the University. Also lots of great restaurants, Whole Foods, and take out nearby. I would definitely recommend this place  to anyone coming to the Austin.

Staying at Alexis's Downtown Oasis (2) was everything we were expecting. The neighborhood is quiet but an easy 10-20 minutes walk to whatever we wanted to do. We really appreciated the snacks she left us, as well as toiletries like sunscreen! Instructions for access and once inside the apartment were very clear and Alexis was extremely responsive to any questions or unexpected issues. The beds were comfortable and the apartment immaculate. We had a lovely stay!

Alexis was very responsive, open, and welcoming from the time we made our reservations to the time we checked out! My dad was visiting from out of state and wanted to stay a bit closer to town than my house, so we booked Downtown Oasis 2. My dad is an older gentleman who had never heard of Airbnb before and was skeptical, but after our excellent stay in Alexis' condo I think he's converted! He kept saying "Alexis really thought of everything!" and it couldn't be more true - everything you need is in this condo, from free snacks and beverages to lawn chairs for the many outdoor concerts/movies/etc that Austin has to offer. If you're looking for a clean, quiet place to stay that's close to the heart of Austin, you can't go wrong here.
Great spot and very comfortable living quarters!!

I truly enjoyed staying at this charming house in Austin. The description of the house is very accurate. The neighborhood is quiet. It was a pleasure to communicate with the owner. She was very kind and even bought and delivered some groceries for me.
If I visit Austin again I will make a reservation for that place again.

My husband and I stayed here for a little bit more than a week. The house was like pictured; very well taken care-of and cozy. The place is very comfortable and nicely decorated. We didn't use any of the appliances, but were glad to be able to use them if necessary. The beds were smaller than we expected, but it was not really a big issue.
The neighborhood was peaceful and conveniently located. We were 10 min. away from the action in South Congress and 15 minutes from Downtown.
Scarlett answered all our messages quickly and kindly. 
This was our first Airbnb experience and overall it was fantastic. The house is great, the neighborhood is nice, and the host is very polite and accommodating. We would absolutely consider staying here again.

The house was way more beautiful than we expected! It had a ton of room and so many cool decorations. It was the perfect walking distance to food like Torchy's and such an easy commute to downtown. I couldn't have stayed at better place; lots of parking, great utilities, super sweet and accommodating host, and incredibly cute chickens in the backyard!! Would definitely stay here again and recommend others to do so too.

My wife and I live near Austin and visit a lot. We've had lots of AirBnBs in Austin and are pretty familiar with the good, bad, and ugly in the area. This time around, we had a friend with us and needed two rooms. Jeremiah's place was pretty much the best I've seen in Austin with regard to this requirement. VERY spacious and plenty of room to get some privacy from other guests. No "one bed and a comfy couch" business here. Two full-sized bedrooms with quality beds (another rarity as far as AirBnBs go). A very competitive price, too.

The only knock, and it's a slight one, is location. The place is actually very close to places you might want to visit (S. Congress, 6th street, etc.), but you do need to get across I-35. A 5 minute drive. Not a big deal for us, as we had a car, but if you are militant about walking and not taking the occasional cab or Uber, you probably want to inch a bit closer. IMO, Austin is a sprawling city, and it's hard to see the best stuff only on foot. The real suggestion would be to modify your travel plans to not be limited to only foot travel.

More good stuff to complete the compliment sandwich: Jeremiah's place is *immaculate.* Very, very clean with any toiletries you might expect. Again, things that are commonly neglected in AirBnBs. He also left the cupboard full of refreshments and accoutrements (coffee, water, beer, extra towels, etc.) which was really thoughtful. We had great communication leading up to the trip, and he was very invested in ensuring we had a great time in Austin. Easy, flexible, and relaxed checkout. Highly recommended.
Great, spotless property. Very efficient communicator. Fantastic experience.
Esteban's place is awesome!  Great location, super quiet, and even has the option for a fire outside.  Really enjoyed my stay - thanks!

This place is absolutely BEAUTIFUL! There are so many great things this house has to offer. It really gives you the feeling of being somewhere different, but is not lacking "cozy" decorations like most rental properties. There is a wonderful balcony to sit and look at the lake. And most importantly, the  beds are more comfortable than my own bed at home! Our host was amazing. Very easy to get in touch with and very anxious to help us in any way possible. We had never been to Austin before so we had many questions and all of them were answered quickly and with enthusiasm! I would highly recommend staying at this lake Travis house!

The place is in a convenient part of Austin, right by the major freeway. Kunal was flexible in checking in and out and very thorough with instructions. Place could have been cleaner and more guest friendly but everything else was great.

What a delightful stay. The cozy little spot was as beautiful as the city, itself. I spent a fair bit of time in the room, chilling out on my vacation, but it was extremely easy to walk out and find fantastic dining and great culture just a few steps away. And Cindy ‚Äî don't get me started on how welcome Cindy made me feel. She had guides and snacks awaiting me, and she walked me through all the ins and outs of the location, from the room itself to the neighborhood. This isn't a complaint, but you should know that the room is, indeed, small. That was fine for me, but it wouldn't be great for a family.

Although I could not make it for this stay, my friend Courtney who I was planning on going with still went. She wanted to say "It was great! The apartment was clean, great location for all the downtown Austin events, she was great to work with as a renter. She was sweet and understanding. My favorite part was the fresh white roses she had on the kitchen. I would rent from her again." Thank you Analisa for making my friend feel welcomed!

Ryan was very accommodating and a great host. The house is well kept and provided a great base for our group while exploring Austin. It's also in a perfect, central location making it easy to check out all areas.

Lovely space! Pictures tell the story. Spent the Thanksgiving holiday with two kids (9 and 3) in total comfort. Close to great food and an easy drive into Downtown. Big enough that we had family over for dinner and enjoyed the quiet neighborhood. Georgia was quick to respond to any and all questions. Great find!
Nice stay. Excellent location. The only thing this studio was lacking was curtains. Really bright at night...
Great place to stay if you are visiting Austin.  Close to everything, really nice condo, comfortable beds, great kitchen, walking distance to restaurants, starbucks, park, and markets.
Location was in a nice neighborhood and the layout of bedrooms is perfect to keep down noise while staying with co-workers.
Great place and location!

The room was nice to sleep in and there were several places to eat nearby.  It was easy getting to and from downtown - personally I alternated between ride shares and walking.  Katherine was a very accommodating host (she was helpful in getting the room ready for my sister on short notice) and was easy to communicate with while I was there.  I enjoyed my stay - it was very easy and hassle-free.

This awesome home was exactly what I needed for a quiet night away (perfect backdrop for weekend-getaways for creative minds). Short drive to downtown, amazing backyard/sanctuary, perfect guest bedroom + bathroom. Entire place was very inviting & extremely clean. Amanda was a great host and I will most def be staying here my next trip to Austin.
Awesome spot! Very relaxing vibes. Even though we didn't get to meet Amanda, she was great with coomunication and made sure everything was ready for us :)

We had an incredible experience! 4 girlfriends and myself stayed here to celebrate 10 years of friendship and sisterhood. We stayed for 4 nights and felt so comfortable in this little gem. The beds, including the fold out couch were delicious to sleep in. The large table was perfect for big breakfasts and game night. The neighborhood itself is charming and beautiful so we took a few hikes there. It's also very close to restaurants and easy to catch a fasten (Austin's version of Uber). Amanda also has a great list of activities and restaurants to check out within walking distance which was SUPER helpful. We would definitely stay here again! Thank you!

Vania and Rey's place was perfect.  we were there for ACL so gone during the day and coming home late at night. they have a separate entrance from their main entrance so it was perfect for late night arrivals. Vania met us with a smile and showed us where the thermometer was and the nearest liquor store! they're close Lyft and Uber rides away from downtown and their neighborhood is super cute.
Sovay's house was a perfect oasis in Austin.  We couldn't have really asked for better accommodations.   I will stay there any time I am in Austin again!

This was my first trip to Austin and I am so happy that we chose to stay here. We were very comfortable in the cottage and felt right at home. The cottage is also in a great location to get to and from downtown, So Co, and Zilker Park.

Comfortable, quiet, convenient cottage in suburban neighborhood near Zilker Park, Barton Springs and various greenbelts.  Easy and quick access to downtown. On-street parking was no problem. Large and well-appointed kitchen is a big plus. Central air and heat. Free wi-fi.

For a price comparable to upscale chains (Hilton, Sheraton) this cottage provides far more room and a far more peaceful and welcoming atmosphere.  The kitchen and sizeable dining area lend themselves well to entertaining if you are in town visiting family or friends. Highly recommended whatever the length of your stay.
Great cottage, amazing location!  Sovay was very easy to work with.  Definitely recommend this enchanting cottage.
A great stay, wonderful location!  Very clean and cute!  Will def stay again when in Austin!

What a perfect little spot in the heart of a great walking district.  The little house was perfectly appointed with all I needed to get going in the morning.  I appreciate it.  Dinners were as easy as walking to the corner.  Don't forget to include a visit to the Dougherty Art Center Gallery when you go there.

Overall, this house a great bungalow a short drive from anywhere in Austin.  My friends and I truly enjoyed the house, especially the open indoor/outdoor concept.  Only negative was the wifi didn't work very well.  I would recommend anyone to stay here.

Incredible 1st experience in a "Tiny House" and I'm looking forward to more in the future. Trish made everything extremely simple and easy, key things when visiting a new city. The unit is in a great and accessible part of town. We were never more than 15 minutes to anywhere we wanted to explore. Austin is a great city and Trish's tiny house is a great place to begin and end any day there.

Trish was a fantastic host! Everything was stocked, clean and ready to go.  Not to mention the tiny house was perfect.  Nice and tiny but the ceilings are tall enough to make you feel like you have more than enough space.  Also, the location is pretty great.  It's a very nice and quiet neighborhood, away from the hustle and bustle of down town, but it's located near enough major roads/free ways that getting anywhere in Austin was so easy, and took so little time as long as traffic was agreeable.  I would stay here again in a heartbeat.

Trish is an absolutely wonderful host and a stellar communicator. She was transparent in all of her interactions with me and responded so quickly to any questions or concerns I had. She takes her business seriously and will do whatever it takes to take care of her guests. 

As for the house itself, I stayed there for 11 days, and my partner was with me for part of that time. I/we loved it! Highly recommended! The house is so cute and has all kinds of character. It's very peaceful, and if you've got a bicycle (as I did), there is secure storage on site. I would highly recommend this lodging for pairs and singles, and if you've got any business downtown or at UT, there are a number of buses that one can catch just one block away. You don't have to use a car to stay here, which is nice because parking and traffic in Austin can be tiresome. Consider making your way around on bike and bus! That's pretty much what we did the whole time. The internet in the house is fast, too. This is a great deal. I plan on staying here again for my next trip to Austin.

We enjoyed our stay in Trish's tiny house!! It was exactly as listed! Trish communicated with us about everything  during our stay. The location made it really easy for us to get around town! My favorite part was the friendly backyard cat :)

Joseph is very top notch, our experience was better than staying at the Hilton!

Communication was also very easy. Highly recommend staying here.

The place was awesome!  Quiet and clean with great amenities. Very close to downtown which was important to me since all my meetings are located there.  Joe was very reachable by text and even came up and introduced himself the night I arrived.  This place would be ideal for work or play!  I plan to bring my wife back for a weekend getaway in the spring.

The location is great. Right in the middle of Austin and a short walk downtown. Hard to beat the location.

With regards to the listing, it is accurate. However, do keep in mind that the pullout couch mattress is incredibly thin and you are better off using the blow-up bed in the room.

There is a kitchen but the pots and pans are not in good shape, and there is also no vent. The windows in the living room also do not open, so there is very little ventilation if you cook. Same goes for the bathroom.

Kyla's place was great and she was an awesome host! We kept in constant communication and there were no problems. The place was impeccably clean and cozy. Quick ten minute ride to downtown. Would definitely stay again. Thanks Kyla!
Good place to spend the night with a nice view of the lake and great coffee!
Great host and great accommodation.

Chris was very friendly and a great host. He was incredibly helpful in giving us alternative options when we arrived to thunderstorms and some of our outdoor activities were unavailable. He had a handy folder with all the information and walked us through all of the amenities of the beautifully decorated home. The space has a lot of natural light, enough bathrooms for 8 women, a good sized pool to hang out/around/in, and a really cool pinball machine. Chris and Vanessa had prepared a lovely basket of organic snacks for us. We were really close to downtown and a lot of the activities that we had planned. Barton springs was close enough to walk to but we ended up not going due to the rain.

Our airbnb stay in Austin exceeded our expectations and was far better than staying at a hotel. The house comfortably accommodated 4 couples and 2 children.   We were in Austin for a wedding,  from Thanksgiving through the weekend. The house is in a residential neighborhood less than a half mile from I-35 and a short drive to downtown Austin. Vincent Jr. was there for us when we needed him.  The house was well equipped for cooking a thanksgiving dinner and very comfortable.  I would stay there again.
Super easy to work with and very kind! House was nice too.

The space is much bigger than the picture shows, and very comfortable. Best bed to sleep in in Austin! I wish I had gotten to meet Noah in person but our schedules just didn't match up. Instead, I met his super awesome roommates. It was great!
Great location. We were able to walk to the Capital, the university and many other places. Kristen is a divine host. You can't go wrong by choosing to stay at her place.
Martin is a great guy! He is very responsive in his communication and very quick to resolve issues.
Everything worked out great and got all the instructions the day before.

This house is amazing for a large group...very cool wrap around decks on both the first and second floors, two larger master bedrooms, and second floor bunk beds. Brent was great and made everything very easy for check-in and an overall fun stay! I recommend this place for anyone wanting a spacious house in an up-and-coming area of Austin!

Kymberlie was a great host. She provided information to us about Austin, and was always ready to help us with anything we may need.
Her house is very nice and cute and the room was quite private with an ensuite bathroom. That was great.
Also everything In the room was very clean. I definitely recommend Kymberlie and her house for a peaceful stay in Austin.

Location was great.  Being on 6th street was great, due to being able to locate eateries without difficulty . 

Listing was as described.   Very warm and clean.  I would definitely recommend.

Had a little problem with the parking, BUT Chereen was VERY responsive and it was fixed without a hassle.  Chereen was so very easy to deal with and responsive.  THank you Chereen

I am brand new to the whole Air BnB experience and just jumped on the bandwagon ! Luckily, I had a very nice host in Karen , while I stayed in her home in Austin. The home is beautiful and comfy and located in a very nice and safe area in Austin.  I hope that anyone that chooses to stay with Karen and her family will find the same comfort that I did !
This was my first experience using Airbnb... and it was a really great one! This place was super awesome!

Loved our stay in this cozy house. Hosts were responsive and helpful to any questions we had. House location is perfect if you're planning on combining some time spent at Lake Travis and Downtown Austin.
Fantastic place to stay in Austin!  It easily fit four adults and we used it as a launching pad to walk to Franklin BBQ, 6th Street, Rainey Street, and the Capitol.  Highly recommended.
Nice house in a quiet neighborhood off South Lamar.  Austin was very responsive and easy to deal with.  He was also very welcoming of our dogs!

Our family had a fantastic 4 night stay in this home. We were a group of three adults and two children and we found the house so clean, comfortable, and perfect for our needs. It was extremely hot when we visited and the A/C worked great. The mattresses and pillows in all the rooms were so comfortable. Our host was quick to answer any questions we had. Really I can't say enough good things! We would absolutely stay here again if we visit Austin again.
We loved Tami's place. Everything in great condition!

Very nice place. Well kept and beautifully decorated. Also super close to family. Sevylla was very kind and accommodating. Unfortunately we did not get to talk to her much due to our schedule for that weekend. I would consider staying there again. :)

The loft was super clean, comfortable and well equipped. We were there for a music festival and used lyft to get around. The location of the loft is perfect. Great communication with the owner and great experience overall!!
Clean and cozy apartment with great proximity to Rainey and the rest of downtown. Would definitely stay here again

We really enjoyed our stay! The condo was spacious for being right downtown, and the view was fabulous. We were able to easily walk to restaurants and bars. TopTrip made it smooth for us to check in, park, and get settled. We really appreciated our host leaving us a bottle of wine and snacks.
Absolutely zero complaints. Location was perfect, very clean and nice, had set up for netflix, and was very quick to respond.

My friend and I rented this space for a long weekend trip to Austin and were more than satisfied with the experience. Bill was a great communicative host. The space was gorgeous and filled with everything we could have needed: very comfortable bed, bathrobes and towels, espresso maker, magazines about Austin and bicycles, to name a few. The location is also perfect. Just a few blocks from the activity of South Congress and a bus line that will take you quickly downtown for a dollar. I would definitely stay here again and recommend it to others. Thanks, Bill and Dora!

Our stay at the Carriage House was great. The apartment was clean, decorated beautifully, and was everything we wanted in our weekend get away. It's nestled in a quiet neighborhood in Soco and we were an Uber ride a way from everything.  Our host provided us with coffee for the morning and a large tv we could watch in the most comfortable King bed! Overall, a fantastic experience.
Very convenient location. Quiet, clean, and very close to downtown. I would stay here again.

We were greeted, welcomed, and shown around. The unit is very clean, newly finished, modern decor. Came with all the necessities, including shampoo etc. Also had coffee, fruit, water, and juice available for us. Comfy beds too. We really enjoyed our stay!
The location was great. The place was great. Clean and comfortable. Duane was very accommodating of a weird arrival time and very friendly. Highly recommended!

My stay at Duane's place was perfect!  He was extremely accommodating, and wonderful host.  The location was great, and communication with him was awesome.  I would have no issue staying at his place again.
The place was in a comfortable location ‚Äì just 20 minutes from Austin Downton. There was a really nice bagel place just next to it. The place had definitely it's own atmosphere, and a great view.

Stew was great and timely in all his responses. Very down to earth, helpful, and easy to get along with. The apartment is a private suite above his garage. It has been nicely renovated. Fully stocked kitchen. Lots of privacy. Easy access to all of Austin.
Great host, made everything very easy for my stay and the apartment was a short drive from 6th street

Jirir made us feel very welcomed and he gave us a tour of the condo and building so he was sure we knew our way around the place. The condo and location were as described, both the condo and location are great! He had a notebook there with everything you needed for the condo and building plus place with maps to go to in the Austin area. We would definitely stay there again when we are in Austin.
Jordan's place is great! He is a super accommodating host, his apartment is beautiful and in a great location, in walking distance from a bunch of restaurants and bus stops. Definitely recommend! :)

Justin was awesome! Super welcoming, gave us access to everything in his house, and bought us a case of beer.! The house was clean and tidy, and air mattresses were a huge plus with 6 people.  The neighborhood was great with only a $10 uber to downtown.  I'd stay here again in a heart beat.
The host greeted us on arrival and was very helpful. The cottage was very nice decorated and was close to soco. Perfect place for a couple to spend the weekend.

Sovey was awesome! My girfriend and I stayed in Sovey's house for 6 days while I found an apartment in Austin. Sovey made sure we were always okay and even stopped by on my first day to town  to make sure I was settling in nicely. Her home was so cute and clean + it was the perfect amount of space for my friend and I. We were able to use the kitchen for breakfast and lunch + watch movies on her huge tv screen while we lounged in her comfy bed! I highly recommend her space to anyone. It's so close to the city and Gourdough's(the best donuts I've ever eaten!)
This was the first time my husband and I stayed at this location. It was very comfortable, spacious, clean and chic. Sovay's attention to detail is astonishing. Highly recommend.

Sovay was a great host; she provided a large amount of information about the area including attractions, restaurants, etc. The bungalow has a good location, only about 10 minutes from the capitol building! Everything was clean, the amenities were great. Would stay there again.
It was a beautiful room in a great part of town, where there was always something to do. Amanda was great about reaching out to us if we needed anything and made us feel welcomed.

Had a great stay during SXSW music -- comfortable, clean, and very quiet, perfect after a long day in the crowds.  Jason was super helpful and responsive.  Walkable (~20 mins) from 6th street, with easy access to bus and car2go.  I would definitely stay here again.

David and Charles were great hosts, making me feel welcome in their home and their kitchen. The bedroom and bathroom were absolutely clean and well furnished. The neighborhood was quite. The pool was lovely and warm enough for a Pacific NW visitor to enjoy floating in. And Peanut and Gigi (their dogs) were a pleasure to spend time with.

Had a terrific stay at her place in Austin. The living space was clean and  comfortable for 6 people. The bathroom and bedrooms were spacious and adequate. The front door has a keypad lock which makes logistics much easier with big groups. 
The highlight is the proximity to Rainey Street with the night life and restaurants. Highly recommend to other travelers.
It was a great house!  Great location and very clean!

Steven was an extremely accommodating and easy to work with host. He helped me out with directions and even reminded me that I had left a pair of shoes. His house is amazingly modern. The picture don't do it justice. The neighborhood it is located in is very trendy and urbane. Easy access to all sorts of things that Austin has to offer. Downtown is maybe 5 minutes away.
