It's honestly an amazing location. 
The room is gigantic and as described really a "masters suite". This eclipses the Ritz Carlton or St. Regis hotels as the room of thus size would be thousands. High speed Internet, large California King bed. Modern restroom, very clean. Again this was my first Airbnb, and I am inclined to use him again. The location is well worth it and the hospitality from him was better than any hotel you stay at. 
I encourage anyone looking for a optimally located, urban, modern, safe and trendy location in central/downtown Austin to book it! 
Thanks again will definitely book again!

This was such a great home to rent. We had 7 people and were incredibly comfortable. This place is immaculate and our two young children had a blast in the 3rd floor play area/tree house outside. The kitchen is beautiful, the house is clean, the beds are comfortable. None of us had any complaints whatsoever. They had an incredibly helpful guidebook and even had a welcome basket full of goodies. We would stay here again in a heartbeat!

Nathalie was very communicative and made sure we had everything we needed during our stay. The house was clean and had everything we needed during our trip in Austin.

Thanks again!

Had an amazing stay at Loy and Jess's. They are professional and efficient as hosts. We would highly recommend this place for its  central location  and great value. Online description was accurate.  A great find!
The hosts made us feel welcome.  They made sure we had everything we needed in order to have a pleasant stay.  It was a peaceful home located on a quiet street.
Great place to stay at a great price.   Clean, cozy, quiet  two bedroom that's been newly remodeled. Definitely an A+
Nice garage apartment. Close to downtown and S Congress. Very friendly and accommodating hosts.

This place is comfy, clean, well decorated, and quiet. Josh handed me the key promptly despite of my late arrival. The heating system was very quiet (I'm sensitive to noises so this was a definite plus), but heats up the entire place super fast. Bed was comfortable. Bathroom clean. Kitchen well-equipped. I'd definitely stay here again if I come back to Austin someday.

Robert was very prompt with his responses to my questions and made the stay easy and relaxing. The house was in a great location and furnished well. Very cool artwork throughout the house and a very chill patio area fenced-in for privacy. Would definitely stay here again!
Had fun visiting friends in Austin and being close to E 6th, Rainey, and downtown! Great check-in and check-out flexibility. We greatly enjoyed our stay.
The view is awesome. Really close to 6th st.

Very cozy room in a nice house. Easy access to downtown with transit or rental car. Susana and partner Bradley were essentially invisible during our stay, but available by airbnb app. At time of writing (7/19/16) uber/lyft were not in city, but two other ride share apps (fare and fasten) were available. Floors were dirty, but sheets & towels were fresh and rooms were well kept. Overall very nice stay.

Angella's home was perfect for our weekend stay. This is an ideal place for small groups looking for a base in Austin. Angella is an outstanding host and made us feel right at home. She communicated very well at check-in and check-out. She created a welcome guide complete with information about the area, restaurants, things to do, etc. She also had prepared snacks and drinks when we arrived. Her place is in a great location between downtown and the airport making transportation no problem. The keypad on the door was also a nice touch, and free parking in the driveway. I would absolutely stay here again and believe I will because I loved my first time in Austin!
Jacob's place is the perfect weekend getaway right in the heart of Austin. It was clean, spacious, and the view of the capitol building cannot be beat.

Raquel & Jacob's place was perfect for our family trip to drop off our son at college. The location was in the heart of the city‚Äìwe easily walked to 6th street to get ice cream. As mentioned, The loft has a killer view of the State Capital, just a block away. Clean simple amenities. Great Hosts‚Äì Raquel even went above and beyond, contacting me the day before our stay and offering a larger loft for the same price to make sure our family was comfortable! That's service! Thanks guys.
Great hosts, friendly and accommodating. Will definitely visit again.

Andrew was a great host during ACL weekend.  They house was amazing, very clean and spacious for 7 people.  Convenient and close to downtown.   I highly recommend Andrew's place for anyone visiting Austin.

Julie and Rick were awesome! Their property and trailer is a great way to get out of the city and enjoy some quiet relaxation! They were more than accommodating with us and our two pups! It was clean, and close to their own home so we felt a little safer staying in the area. It was a great little getaway!
Tyler was super communitive throughout the booking and my arrival process. He's got great taste in music and you can't really beat the location!

Tyler was a great host. He gave really clear instructions on getting to the house. The location was great, there are restaurants within five minutes walk. Everything in the house is clean and neat and easy to find, we had a lovely stay at the house. I would definitely recommend this place :)

The hosts were very welcome. They helped us out in planning our visit to Austin. Very prompt in responding to texts. Very friendly. Nice and cosy house. I would love to stay here again if I get the chance.

Fantastic location; close to Congress Street and just minutes from downtown.  SUPER comfy beds.  We kind of missed having a living room, but with the rooftop deck & the lower level patio, we were really all set!  Would definitely stay here again; great neighborhood with lots to see within walking distance.
Great space close to downtown Austin. Excellent hosts, had a great stay.

Katie has a lovely home located in a very quite and family friendly neighborhood. I felt completely safe and relaxed during my stay. Her home is right across the street from a shopping center, with a few restaurants, mostly businesses, and a grocery store.

Katie was a wonderful host. She made sure that I was comfortable and had everything I needed for my stay. She is also very helpful and offered suggestions for things to do or how to navigate around Austin.
We loved our stay in Austin. Christina was very helpful and easy to communicate with. The place was great, exactly as described, and an ideal place to base ourselves for our stay in Austin.

Tim's place is absolutely gorgeous. It is better than the ones portrayed in his pictures. We needed to check-in early and Tim was very accommodating and nice to allow us to do so. He is very polite, friendly and a pleasure to get to know. We were not able to spend much time together but was able to chat before we left. I would love to stay there again and hang out with Tim in his beautiful sun room and living room. 

The location of this place is perfect as well. Very beautiful and quiet neighborhood and close to all locations. I would definitely recommend his place to anyone going to Austin.

PS: Both of his dogs are adorable too, and friendly.
My stay was brief, but Tim was great.  His house is very nice.  I was very comfortable.  His dogs are quite pleasant.

My wife and I stayed at Tim's immaculate suite in modern home and it surely was "immaculate." 

The bedroom comes with a large closet and an attached modern bathroom, stocked with all the amenities that previous reviewers have mentioned such as shampoo, conditioner, towels, blow dryer, etc. There is also a wall attached TV in the room with too many cable channels to browse, which was not shown in the photo list. Also, as someone mentioned in the other review, the bed is super comfortable. 

Tim was generous and flexible to work with. My wife and I were running behind coming from Dallas and weren't going to be able to meet Tim at the time that we agreed upon. I contacted him through airbnb message and he responded promptly. He was very understanding of our situation and worked with us to accommodate our needs. 

Lastly, Tim has two friendly dogs that are very well-behaved.  I regret not having enough time to hang out with them. This was our first time trying airbnb and we were both thoroughly impressed. We only got to stay one night at Tim's, but we shall return. Thanks for being a great host, Tim.
Tim is an excellent host. He has sweet dogs and super cool modern decor. Lots of privacy, healthy breakfast options and great coffee. Excellent experience.
Great place to stay and great location.
Great location, comfy bed, and nice little kitchen. Perfect for out of towners coming to Austin for a workshop or music venue.

Katherine and Andrews home was a wonderful place for my in-laws to stay over the holidays.  They lived the decor and all the amenities.  It was clean, bright and comfortable- probably the best airbnb they've stayed at thus far!
Best airbnb experience everrr!!! Cosy warm friendly welcoming loving space!!! Heaven in Austin!

We had a great time staying at the Treehouse apartment. It was on a quiet and secluded street but with easy access to the highway. Jeff was a great host and very responsive. Would definitely stay here again when traveling in Austin.

Chris and his wife were great hosts, I did not have the pleasure of meeting them, but they left us notes and little surprises (a bottle of wine) to make us feel welcome, as well as being a call and text away for questions. They were so very accommodating, I needed a place the same day as I drove into Austin and they graciously accepted me and got the place ready for us all. When we got there it looked just like the pictures and maybe even a little better. It was clean, and open with comfortable furniture/beds and a kitchen with goodies to help us relax after the long drive in. There were 2 rooms in the house with a patio walkway to an attached 3rd room, all of which were nice and comfortable. The bathroom was very cute and clean, plenty of fresh towels etc. The neighborhood I knew pretty well as I am from Austin, and it was quiet even with lots of new construction going on, on the older homes in the area. It has very easy access to highways and was absolutely a great place to stay. I would definitely stay here again in the future and would recommend it to anyone.
Really nice hosts. Hard time getting a hold of them when needed. But the house was beautiful and absolutely amazing. Would rent from again!

We had a great experience at this residence. Absolutely perfect for our week at SXSW. Spacious, clean, and well-kept. It's also very close in proximity to near-by restaurants, short drive downtown Austin, and the neighborhood is very nice. Highly recommended!
Place was nice. Check in was easy. Larry was great. Close to Rainey. What else can you ask for? Definitely a great experience.

The place was really nice and beautiful. It really is a home away from home. It is located in a very quiet and quaint area but within walking distance from where most of the things are located. Restaurants , bars , coffee shops are literally right in front of the doorsteps but amazingly very quiet and nice once inside the house. The kitchen is equipped with everything you need even more than what most people have in their kitchen. House has washer and dryer... beds are comfortable... TV... this listing is beautiful... James was nice and very accommodating to our check in time and check out time since we arrived at a late hour. 6th street was less than 9$ if you use Uber... if you drive, it is literally within 1-5 mile radius from everywhere... this house is awesome and definitely +++++++++   everything was perfect!

Wow! This was such a great place to stay! Awesome house in a great central neighborhood! So many nice little design touches, and perfectly set up for hosting guests. And the yard is beautiful! I was sad to leave.
Fantastic, couldn't have been better!
Great place with awesome pool. No cable TV or microwave though!

This was my first experience using Airbnb and I was excited by all the really cool places to choose from. I picked Carrie b/c she was close to where I was headed next morning and b/c of her pup, Artie. First off, Artie is awesome! Second, Carrie was too! Super nice and easy-going. The room was perfect---most comfortable bed! Wish I had gotten more time to lounge in it! Bath across the hall was perfect for me. I did not sleep well but it was b/c I was afraid I wouldn't wake up at  the hour I had to get up. There was a box fan for me to use b/c her ceiling fan was not working, but I have to have the white-noise so it was perfect for me. Looked like a fun neighborhood but I was there for a conference w/o time to explore.   Hope to visit again!

Alexa's place was perfect! Upon arrival there was no need to try and coordinate with the host to get into the apartment since there is coded access. The apartment was comfortable and clean! The location was great, close (driving distance) to downtown and good places to eat.
The studio was really nice, pretty convenienct location. We ended up leaving early due to heavy rains and Erica refunded part of our fee for the night the same day, she was really great!

Marnie was such a gracious host, perfect communicator. The home is a little piece of magic nestled in quiet neighborhood. it was the perfect place to stay to escape the madness of SXSW. i only wish i could have took advantage of the amazing yard and kitchen. the beds are perfect and both showers are great. i highly recommend this home if your in town for business or  visiting austin with your family.

The listing description was right on target.  My 3 guests really enjoyed our stay at Eric's awesome home.  The location was so perfect and the house was clean, cute, and I felt totally comfortable there! Eric replied to me very quickly and even helped us out by letting us in early that day! I completely recommend Eric and his place!

I stayed at Eric's place with my husband and a couple of our friends for 3 nights.  Eric's place was just perfect for us!  He was so welcoming.  

A few days before our arrival he sent me and email with a list of recommended things to do in the area  (restaurants, nightlife, etc).  I know there is TripAdvisor and Yelp and such out there, but I really appreciated this extra step he took.  It was really nice to get an insider's perspective. 

The house itself was great.  The bed I slept on was actually so comfy that I had to ask him what brand it was so I could get one for myself (for real!).  There was a Keurig type coffeemaker which was super awesome along with the to-go containers he provided.  That made it easy to make a cup of coffee to take with us while exploring the city.  Plenty of things in the kitchen to use (pans, plates, utensils, etc.).

We got a good amount of use out of the Roku in the living room too.  We polished off a season of Food Truck Wars on Netflix during our stay :)

Also loved the porch!

There are fans in every room, so don't worry about ever feeling too hot.  I actually felt a bit chilly one night despite the 95 degree days we had

The neighborhood was quiet with an elementary school nearby, but still in walking distance (8-12 min) from some good eats.  You can get most everywhere in an Uber for $6-$10.

Eric stopped by a couple of times to see if there was anything we needed.  I thought that was really nice of him to do!

All in all it was a really great experience for our first stay with an AirBnB.  Thanks!!

Loved our stay in Tiffany's loft! We felt at home right away in her comfortable, cozy space. It was clean and very nicely decorated. Tiffany was an accommodating host who was very easy to get in touch with. Just a short drive from downtown and the fun shops on South Congress. Would definitely stay again!
Amazing, secluded BNB with plenty of wildlife. Great little place to launch your adventures from! Within range of downtown and parks.

This was an easy/quick spot to stop and sleep for the night in Austin. It was my first time being in a commercial Airbnb scenario and it was a big letdown. I felt very mislead regarding the shared nature of the space. The host company seems comfortable posting the "private room" details but wasn't willing to mention the SHARED living room, kitchen, and bathroom setting. Heads up: YOU MAY BE SHARING THIS SPACE WITH ANY OLD JOE SMOE THAT BOOKS ANOTHER ROOM IN THE HOUSE!!!
This place was really cool, super close to downtown, and everyone was super accommodating. Would totally stay here again.

Paula's place is indeed a charmer, and so is Paula! This was my first experience renting a room with Airbnb; I have always rented an entire home or apartment in the past, so I wasn't sure what to expect. However, Paula made it an absolutely wonderful experience. Everything was as described or even better, and I felt right at home. Paula's home is clean and inviting, my bed was really comfortable, and being able to use the kitchen is a bonus. The neighborhood is quaint and felt very safe. Paula was extremely welcoming and accommodating, but at the same time, very respectful of my privacy and needs. And, if all that wasn't enough, coffee on the deck each morning in the midst of a lovely greenspace was an unexpected and special treat. Great experience!!! Thank you, Paula!!!

Our house manager Laura was literally there every step of the way, even calling up with alternative strategies after Uber and Lyft cancelled their service a couple days before we arrived. She was awesome, we were treated extremely well. 

We were 10-14 guys on a guys weekend and ended up renting Boho Chic as well, which is the adjoining house laid out in almost exactly the same way.

It's about a 5-10 walk from Rainy street which has an awesome bar scene and great late night truck options. 

The only downside was that it was hot and they didn't have a pool, but that did force us to go to Barton Springs which was a great experience. 

Note: all of the beds are queens or kings so you'll be doubling up if you have a big group.
I highly recommend staying at Ashley's place. It is soooo close to everything! Very comfortable, felt at home and a very attentive hostess!

Perfect place to experience the famous, unique Austin culture while also close to some very awesome hiking spots and paddle boarding on the river. Ryan was very welcoming, like we were close friends visiting for the weekend. Would stay here again if I ever made another trip to Austin!

8 of us stayed at Moya's while in Austin for a wedding last weekend.  The house is quite large - the bedrooms are spread across three floors and we all fit there comfortably.  As someone mentioned below, the only full bathrooms are connected to the 3 bedrooms on the third floor, so we had to accommodate the downstairs guests in that regard.  The basement has a few sleeping areas, but they are not separated by real walls or doors.  The house was very clean and quiet, as was the street.  We really enjoyed the pool and the hot tub.

There's a minimart just across the street, and the house is about a 2 minute drive to Lamar Road where there are a ton of restaurants, stores, things to do and about a 10 minute drive to downtown Austin/Congress Street, so the location was really unbeatable.  We had a few issues - figuring out how to reset the hot tub, and turning on the hot water for the master bathroom shower - but Moya was very responsive when we called or texted her.  It was a great stay and I'd certainly stay here with a group of friends again.

Alan was a wonderfully accommodating & helpful, hands-down-best-airbnb-host-EVER! I almost don't want to write this review because I want to keep this gem hidden away! Lots of things, both food and recreation, are in walking distance to Alan's home in the heart of Austin - though, we did end up mostly driving our rental car to explore the city. He also gave us several recommendations and helped us anytime we needed ANYthing - whether it was Pepto Bismol, a hole puncher, or cookie sheets! We ate at several food trucks (Brunch Haus, Torchy's Tacos), The Salty Sow (twice - it's that good), The Salt Lick for BBQ, Bangers, and several other places I can't recall. Either way, EVERYTHING we ate in Austin was great, plus we went paddle boarding and spelunking in the caves/caverns! So cool. My friend and I stayed for 5 days and are already making plans to come back ASAP. Thanks again, Alan!!! Missing Austin desperately!
Amanada was very friendly and accommodating.

Steve and Monica's place was wonderful! We were in town for a wedding and the first night that we arrived they invited us up on their deck for drinks and gave us advice on where to eat, cool things to do, and what would be a waste of time. It was in a great location and seemed like it was close to everything we wanted to check out. We are big cat lovers so we knew when we saw this rental we had to snatch it up! The cats aren't allowed inside but there are plenty of places to hang out with them outside. The space was perfect for two people, clean, and you can tell that Steve and Monica put a lot of thought into the comfort of their guests. So many little things were provided and very much appreciated. We hope to come back in the future!

Nessa made us feel very welcomed! She was not home when we arrived but was extremely responsive through text and left simple instructions on how to enter the studio. The studio was clean, private, and spacious for two guests. There were plently of places (cafes, restaurants, bars, walgreens) within walking distance on S. Lamar Blvd. It was also really easy ordering a Lyft or Uber to get into downtown. I would definitely stay at Nessa's again.
Best place to stay in Austin! Quiet, comfortable, centrally located and easy access.

This was a great house, just as cute as the photos.  The upstairs bed was very comfy and everything you needed was supplied in the home.  Very clean and great location and meeting Lois made it clear she is very available to help with anything you need.
Great place, walkable to everything in downtown, nice to have a parking space.
Great little loft in a great location. We had a wonderful time in Austin.

Martin's place is a great home base for a weekend out in Austin, right at the edge of UT campus. Martin was incredibly helpful with check-in/check-out info and very quick to respond to any message. Would stay here again!
great
Ashley has a beautiful home and made everything super easy, she was vey communicative, had good Austin recommendations, and we hugely enjoyed staying there.

I wrote a great review and it did not post!  I will try again.  

The description and photos on Angel's house on Comal are absolutely perfectly accurate.  The artsy comfortable house is near the artsy comfortable neighborhood in East downtown Austin, and felt just like we were in our home neighborhood in the Houston Heights. Including the chickens. 

She is a great host and provides more amenities and instant responsiveness than you will need.  All of the guests that I crossed paths with in the house and trailer were all terrific folks. 

The walkable finds nearby were Quickie Pickie, Hillside Farmacy, Take Heart, and Blue Dahlia.

Okay, I even wanted to buy a house nearby in the neighborhood.  :-)
Beautifully updated home in nice neighborhood in North Austin, conveniently located between 1-35 and MOPAC. Comfortable bed with adjacent bathroom, very private.

Il quartiere si trova in un punto strategico,ho raggiunto qualsiasi parte interessante con la mia macchina in 15 minuti.
La casa √® davvero graziosa e la padrona di casa davvero gentile e amichevole e del cane non si √® sentito neanche un rumore essendo molto educato!
Absolutely amazing stay at this Airbnb! Mikelle was very quick to respond and keeps her place very tidy. Images were spot on! Very spacious bedrooms and common area!

comfortable room, very convenient location
adorable and very friendly dogs
Hosts sought to be helpful, although our schedules prevented much contact
We had a great stay at Julian's. Great value for location. Everything was clean and Julian did a great job communicating about how to get in and out. Would totally book again!
Great location, free reign to the house, Adrian is there if you need him but you can really just do your thing. Well worth the stay for the price and location.
Adrian was a great host, able to answer all your questions and very accommodating.
Ali's place is perfectly located, clean, comfortable and beautifully decorated,  she was a great host and easy to communicate with.   If you love Austin as much as I do, you will love this place.
We really enjoyed the bright cottage and neighborhood. Betsy is an exceptionally responsive hostess; her guests are very well taken care of. We will definitely stay again.

Betsy has been very kind and answered all our questions super fast.
The house was cute, with a real sense of vintage decoration, and it was very close to the centre of the city. 
Thank you again Betsy for you kindness and rapidity to deal with issues.

This house had everything we needed and then some! The house and all windows and natural light were so pretty it was hard to leave. Never felt unsafe! And the recommendations in the packet they left us were great. We tried Curra's and loved it! Thanks again!

Sarah was a wonderful and friendly host for us, that's made us comfortable during our stay in Austin, TX. Her responded the our questions very fast. Her dog and cat don't bothering us. It's so nice don't barking don't made loud noise. Her provided everything we could need all the time. This place was perfect, clean, near downtown and very private for us.
Thank you for a great time have a little more conversations with us.
We enjoyed our stay !
Didn't actually get to meet Adan, but the place was ready and clean when I arrived. No complaints. Great for a weekend stay in Austin- a short ride share away from most 'attractions'.
I really enjoyed my stay at Jordan and Julie's.  The room was simple and the bed was really comfortable.  I would gladly stay with this host again.

I really hate writing negative reviews but we did not enjoy our stay. To start with the positives, this is a room in a house in East Austin. 10-20 min walk to all of the highlights of East Austin with shops, restaurants and bars. The outside of the house is cute with a nice kitchen and bathroom-great shower. There is a washer/dryer. The keyless door nobs are handy but a little annoying on your individual room when you close the door to go to the bathroom. This is clearly a house that is solely rented out for Airbnb, no one lives here. So you are missing the locals vibe that is so great about Airbnb. There were other people staying in the other 2 rooms. Interactions with the host are friendly but perfunctory, understandable for the amount of people they probably work with, but not welcoming. The bedroom was the worst part...the rest of the house is clearly invested in but it stops where you sleep. The bed was uncomfortable with minimal, thin blankets. Little to no decorations. Yes, this is a room in a house as advertised but more expensive than a motel room and less nice without your own bathroom. I felt like I was sleeping in a college dorm room or a teenager's unkempt room. Given the location and the common areas, this place has great potential. But until they upgrade the bedrooms, I would not recommend staying here.

I really recommend taking advantage of this Airbnb if you want a simple, clean place within walking distance of good Austin fun. It's located near the East 6th district, with lots of great bars, cafes, coffeehouses, etc. I recommend renting a bike from a nearby shop or B-cycle terminal. 

I barely interacted with the other house guests, but they were friendly!  I had an initial issue with the house codes, but Julia and her team were were on top of taking care of me and I didn't have any further issues. 

I will DEFINITELY stay here again.

I loved to stay with Christian and Blanca these last days! They were amazing with me all the time. Their house is quite charming and comfortable and it is not too far from downtown. It is easy to get there and cheap. There are several buses all day long that go to that direction.
Well, I really appreciated your company and I recommend their house!
You'll have a great time, I bet you will!

Eryn's place is a beautiful, with a great sized bedroom and great bathroom just across the hall. 
If you're a dog person, Eryn has a great, friendly little dog to welcome you when you get home. 
Location is great...nice quiet area, not far from the great bars in east Austin. 
Eryn herself is super friendly, relaxed and super helpful.
Next time in Austin, if Eryn is still hosting, I will be staying again for sure. Thanks for the great stay Eryn.

The house looks just like the pictures, very clean and comfortable. Betty goes out of her way to make sure you have everything you need! I would definitely recommend this place for your stay in Austin.
Very nice accomodations!

Did not end up staying the 2nd night. Was not able to shower due to the handle being broken. I was asked to use a screwdriver to change water temperature but couldn't even get it to turn on. place was dirty. The host said he deep cleaned for 5 hours before I got there after I complained and clearly it could have used 5 more hours. Would not refund the 2nd night even though I had left by 1030am that morning and communicated the conditions were not acceptable.

Jenny and her home were amazing! The bathroom was full of necessities like toothpaste, shampoos, to-go sunscreen and much more. Already trying to plan my next trip to Austin just to stay at this home.
This was our second stay at Belle's guest house.    We enjoyed everything about our visit.  Highly recomended!

just returned from a trip to austin and a stay at aerie guest house. two words: highly recommend! such a great location, such a great, clean little house and such a great host in belle. would absolutely stay there again and again!

Belle was amazing and we thoroughly enjoyed our stay in Austin at her guest house.  She communicated well and was there for us every step of the way.   I hear she's moving and it will be a shame that this place is no longer available.  Hopefully she continues to host when she gets to Denver.  Thanks again belle!

In search for the ideal location for SXSW, I stumbled upon David's place. A true gem in that it provided a peaceful break from the hustle and bustle from the day, but was close enough to hop right back in the action when ready. The place was incredible, and David was a great host, making sure that we were well taken care of during our stay. If you're thinking about coming to Austin, look no further, book immediately! And upon your arrival be sure to make a stop at the taco spot near the house. David is also provided us a great list of other places in the area that were great too. Great location, great hospitality, great stay, 5 stars!
The house was in excellent condition. There are walking trails which are accessible from backyard door.

The house was just like the picture, beautiful. We where 5 adults and a toddler and the place was super comfortable for all of us. Everything was clean and the brand new deck was a perfect spot to hang out. We where super close to downtown and great other places to visit and eat. Definitely a will booked Eric house again

Very warm, we had the chance to meet Devang and Gavin too, they were very nice guys and always asking if we needed something, the room and hosts allowed us to have enough privacy! And the price was good too!, thanks for having us guys!
Great place to stay. Quiet neighborhood close to the city.

The sunny little cottage apartment perfectly met my needs for a quiet, cozy spot to spend a a couple of days in a wonderful Austin neighborhood. The location is ideal if one wants to get out of the fray for downtime, yet be able to hop on a major thoroughfare for quick access to the hustle and bustle. I took walks around the neighborhood and down to Mozart's on the lake for smoothies. The nearby Deep Eddy Pool was refreshing. But I have to admit I had a difficult time getting out of the house; it was so comfortable and pleasant, complete with fresh fruit, yogurt and water provided by Kelly. 

Kelly was very welcoming and kind and made everything so easy. She was responsive and also left me alone to come and go. I enjoyed my visit quite a bit and hope to return for perhaps a longer stay another time.

My son and I had a lovely experience staying here. The place was clean, cozy and equipped with everything we needed for our short stay. We arrived late at night, so we were delighted when we saw see all of the breakfast items that Kelly left for us for the following morning (coffee, eggs, butter, milk, yogurt, muffins and fruit). Kelly was a gracious host. One afternoon, I arrived with bags of groceries and was walking with my two-year old son to the back of the property where the cottage is located, when Kelly and one of her friends came out of her home to help us carry the groceries upstairs. She later invited us to socialize with some of her friends who were visiting, which is never expected with airbnbs  but was so appreciated, as I'm a single mom and was traveling alone with my son. The neighborhood is very tranquil, close enough to central Austin (about a 5-minute drive to downtown), but away from all the noise and traffic. It really was a nice retreat! We would definitely stay here again.

This is a really great home especially for the price you pay, we really enjoyed our stay at Donna's. The neighborhood is quiet and toward the end of your stay you'll feel like this is your own home. Thank you again Donna!
It was cozy!

This is the second time to stay in this house. The host is so kind and there is no problem to check in. The same so much more convenient for me to do everything including cooking. It's worth highly recommended for everyone to travel Austin.

Erwin has the perfect Airbnb setup - great location, a lot of space,  comfortable bed and amenities. He's a fantastic host, too - well traveled, kind, humble, thoughtful, and always looking for ways to improve. Highly recommended for any Austin stay!

Ashley describes the apartment as big and cozy, and she isn't kidding in either respect. It's definitely big and cozy! Great decor and very charming. Big, comfortable bed. The place is pretty clean and organized. Nice little private backyard area. There is a parking spot right in front of the apartment, which is convenient. The place is about 2 miles from downtown Austin - everything seems to be about a 10 minute drive away from her apartment. Ashley is very sweet and hospitable. Even though she was really busy while I was staying there, she made sure to respond to all text messages and emails promptly, to ensure that I had a comfortable stay. Thanks, Ashley!

What a fantastic place to stay. The location was amazing and the place had character. It has this sort of Urban Outfitters kind of vibe going. The place is very accommodating to pets (small back yard and a nice neighborhood to walk in). Ashley was a wonderful hostess, easy to get a hold of, and gave great recommendations. Very glad I met her and I would highly recommend this place to anyone.
listing was accurate, great hosts, very chilled. Comfortable room with very fast wifi!

Our stay at Tyler's place was just okay. The pros were the ideal location and the comfortable bed. The photos are mostly accurate, but he also has lots of his own personal belongings all throughout the house that are not in the photos. We spent lots of time trying to get our young kids not to touch all of his things on the floors, tables and against the walls. Also, it's not super clean or tidy. There were huge stains on the the couches, the rugs were dirty and the blinds in the bedroom were held up with tape and kept falling down. Probably not a bad choice for a bachelor party, but not ideal for a family.
Great condo, Perfect location. Ryan is extremely accommodating and just a great host. Book it!

This was a great place. Gorgeous high ceilings and on stilts (i think) --my good  friend informs me this is how houses used to be built to minimize the effects of heat. Anyway I was surprised and impressed by how high the ceilings were. Full of character, walking distance to a great wine store, delicious restaurants, and a fun screened in porch. The place is beautifully decorated--there have been really cool updates since some of the posted pictures like a great metal table and different closet coverings. Tons of amenities to make you feel at home. Cindy is on top of everything--you couldn't ask for anyone nicer or more attentive to detail. The place is sparkling clean. We wanted to stay the whole time but Cindy was pretty booked up--I'm so glad we were able to stay a couple of nights!

Kris' place was spacious, clean, and homey. The bathroom was easily accessible/very clean. The location is only 10-15 away from downtown, which is very convenient. Kris was nice and helpful, would stay again.

We had a great time at SXSW and this was partly due to the great experience we had staying with Kade. His house is perfectly situated - 10min walk to the Convention Center and on the way is the food truck parking lot!

The house is medium sized and very comfortable for 4-6 people. We were only 3 and wished we had invited a couple more people.

We hope to stay with Kade again next year!

Had a great stay. Did not meet my host but he was very responsive to texts and we had no issues getting in or settled. Location was nice with both proximity to the river trails for a morning jog and moderate walking distance to downtown. Also a great vegan taco truck around the corner. Would stay again!

Absolutely great! Perfect place to explore Austin from, easy to park outside, really cozy interior, and a nice front porch to kick back on. We loved the city and Susan's place, and we'd love to return anytime.

The house was exactly as advertised.  Clean and ready for arrival.  The location couldn't be better, walking distance to many of Austin's best restaurants!  Susan was an excellent host!  We will definitely stay there again!

Cory was great meeting me on arrival and working around my flight schedule. The apartment was clean, quite and had a nice sunny window off the kitchen. It made good home base located close to Continental  Club and just a 15 minute walk to the Convention Center.

Our stay here was great! The home is super cute and comfortable. It fit six of us without feeling crammed (granted there is only one bathroom). A little welcome basket was waiting for us, which was very thoughtful. And communicating with the host was extremely easy and they were very accommodating.

This place is such a gem!!! Sara was so accommodating since the moment I inquired about the Spartan Mansion. The detailing that was put into the decor and the overall esthetics is beyond explainable! Everything was VERY clean, very cute and the the record collection was on point! Thank you so much Sara for letting us stay there. We can't wait to go back!

Our stay at Angela's exceeded our expectations. The home is beautifully decorated, clean, and in a quiet neighborhood. Angela and Jim were very helpful and had great suggestions for restaurants and shopping. I would highly recommend staying at Easy Living!

La maison de Sat est relativement grande ! Parfaite pour accueillir huit personnes ! Il a √©t√© tr√®s arrangeant quant √† l'horaire de notre arriv√©e et lorsque nous avons eu besoin de lui il s'est montr√© imm√©diatement disponible. Nous recommandons vivement ce logement !

Residential neighborhood right outside 35. Great location close to major highways so it makes getting around a lot more convienient. House was very inviting, enough space for five adults. Large backyard was also nice. Would reccomend in the future!

We had a lot of fun at the Motel Camper - the outdoor movie area was a huge highlight for us! We only stayed for one night, so didn't take advantage of a lot of the thoughtful amenities offered, but the bed was very comfortable.
Great place, quiet, and close to everything in town.

Cute house in a very good location.  Mary left bottled water and coffee for us, which is really appreciated -- usually rentals come with nothing in the kitchen.  House has been renovated very well; lots of privacy and comfortable furniture and beds.  Will definitely stay with Mary again when we return to Austin.
Great location
Good experience, easy to communicate, fast responses and all as mentioned. safe, clean and very quiet. Centric zone & easy to parking. Many txs Shea.

Shea's place was an excellent home-base for our visit to Austin. Even though it's a little far from the city, it was only a $12 Uber to downtown, and the parking was a major plus. Very clean place, and Shea is a nice, chill host.
I enjoyed my stay. This was my first time using Airbnb. It was a good experience.

The house was perfect for ACL! You get exactly what's in the listing (and not one of those pictures-were-better-than-real-life situations) which was pretty awesome. John was great at giving updates with matters concerning the rental. Thank you for a great experience!
Great location with a clean living space. Personally was a huge fan of the backyard area very chill. If I'm ever in the area I know where I want to stay at.

We really enjoyed our stay.  The description and pictures are spot on.  A very tranquil and peaceful retreat-like bungalow constructed of cool reclaim materials and decorated with interesting and eclectic items from around Texas....Very Austin!
The bungalow retreat is basically a separated backyard to her main home set in a normal neighborhood with quick access to everything.  We had zero issues with any noise from neighbors or the 2 car metro style trains (sounded like trolleys not freight trains).  Parking was right in her driveway, perfect!
Trudy was very good with the reservation and communications and made us feel very welcome.  She also made herself available but gave us our privacy.  Trudy really knows how to welcome guests with personal touches like coffee/tea/popcorn, staged linens, citronella candles, food for the goldfish, etc...She offers a professional grade product and service.  Next time we visit our son at UT this is our place to stay!

Amanda & Greg's place was perfect for our family trip to ACL!
The house was in great condition and location was great for shopping and dining near by!
Great location with plenty of good eating around. Clean home with comfy beds. I didn't get a chance to use the hot tub, but aim to come back next time I'm in town.
L'endroit est tr√®s joli, propre et accueillant! Les h√¥tes sont tr√®s sympathiques!  Super s√©jour √† Austin!

Jeannie is a fantastic host.  The place is just as described.  The studio is comfortable and quite.  The property is located in one of my favorite places in Austin - Stacy Park.  Beautiful trails and a swimming pool that is open year round.  I certainly recommend the place to any traveler interested in Austin's central core.

Jeannie was a great host. The apartment was very thoughtfully furnished and comfortable. Appreciate Jeannie's hospitality. Would gladly stay again.

Thanks!
Patrice and Daniel were very generous and friendly hosts, and we had a great (EMAIL HIDDEN)munication was also top-notch. When back in Austin, we'd certainly return.
Charley's house was perfect for 6th street fun. I think its only about a 10 min. drive and very easy to get to. Great house and very clean!!

The house was cozy, trendy and well maintained.  The large yard was perfect for our dog to hang out. The location was perfect! Nice neighborhood and very close to many restaurants, shopping and downtown.  I would definitely recommend this place to others. Host communicated early and often to ensure our stay was as smooth as possible.
House as appears in the pictures. Lauren was a good host and made us feel welcome and comfortable. Centrally located, many things within walking distance or short cab ride.

Andy and Ellen's cottage was just right for us. The kitchen is handy and the provisions were generous and thoughtful. The neighborhood is quiet and comfortable and convenient to major transportation routes. I would recommend it to any Austin visitors and would happily stay there again.

Andy and Ellen are wonderful hosts and we thoroughly enjoyed our accommodations at their cottage. Andy took care of a problem with one of the bikes ASAP and got us back up riding quickly. The collection of books in the cottage had lots of great information about Austin and surrounding areas. The breakfast goodies they provided were very thoughtful. We felt very much at home during our visit there. You probably can not find a better place to stay in Austin.
I enjoyed my stay at TurnKey rentals. The apartment was clean and had everything I needed. I will definitely return next time I'm in Austin.

Cottage was perfect. Great location, very clean, comfy bed, essentials in the kitchen and even a few good beers in fridge. Much appreciated!! Dawn was great when we asked for local suggestions while at the same time giving plenty of privacy.  Definitely recommend.

What a cute and perfect place for a nice long weekend getaway.  Dawn was incredibly kind and the place felt like home.  After returning from my first night out I found water and snacks.  What a nice surprise that was considering I did not bring anything with me.  The next morning instead of scrambling to find food there were oatmeal packets.  It was fantastic to lounge in bed for a little longer.  I would recommend this place to anyone looking to feel at home immediately.

Awesome place: clean house, super nice host. Highly recommended. As a tourist, I actually found the location quite convenient with a couple bus stops 5 minutes away (bus 6 will get you to the Capitol in around 20 minutes).

Adam and Ike were great hosts. They ensured we had a hilarious starter pack to prepare us for our time in Austin, listing out their favorite restaurants, bars, and activities. We enjoyed the location as it was a short drive or uber ride to anything and everything we wanted to do. Even after the stay, Adam and Ike were extremely thoughtful in mailing a piece of jewelry left behind on accident.
Erin made us feel welcome and she was very accommodating. Her home is lovely and provided everything we needed while in the city. Please don't hesitate to book your stay here.

The Annex was perfect for our trip to Austin. It was only minutes away from the festival we were attending and lots of other fun things, including Barton Springs! The space had everything we needed and more! The fridge was stocked with juice, a full brita, lots of fruit, potatoes from Jeff and Cindys garden, delicious organic milk and even some beer! There were lots of extra pillows and blankets, a coffee pot (with coffee!), plenty of space to unpack our things, lots of towels (including those for the Barton Springs pool) and a beautiful view out into the garden. We used the bikes to get to the festival on the river and it was super convenient, not too mention a beautiful ride through Zilker. Jeff and Cindy were incredibly gracious hosts and even stayed up to let us in and show us around when we got in at 2am. They went above and beyond to make sure we had everything we needed. The Annex is a beautiful and sustainable AirBnb with accommodating and flexible hosts. I will absolutely be booking here for my next trip to ATX!

Everything was great at The Zilker Experience! The location is excellent and in a great little neighborhood that is walkable and convenient. We had a car so used that as well. Street parking was plentiful. Everything was clean and exactly as expected. The bed was super comfortable too! Excellent experience here!

Rick responded to my texts for information and provided us with the few items we needed and couldn't find when asked.
Loved the neighborhood and the market nearby was perfect for snacks, beer and wine, breakfast tacos and COFFEE ... although there was a keurig coffee machine in the apartment.)
Great cottage, well stocked, good for pets fenced in back yard.  Hot water was a little inconsistent.  The store across the street was great for quick needs.  Nice neighborhood and friendly neighbors
Great experience, very clean. Wonderful host. The dogs are awesome and so well behaved. Everything was smooth and hassle free and just as described. Thank you.
Staying at this house was great. It's got a lot of character. Communication from Emmilou was clear and prompt. All in all a very good experience!

Duane lives up to his Super Host rating! He was easy and professional to communicate before the trip, offered excellent recommendations and gave us plenty of privacy. The room is great for a few friends traveling together and very accessible to the bustling East Side.
Nice place and host. We had a great experience. The location is great. There are lots of restaurants and bars near by. Nice clean room, wonderful matress, and adorable dogs.

The place is in a quiet residential area just a couple of blocks south of the best of South Congress which is my favourite area in Austin. I stayed during SXSW, when finding accomodation is a nightmare, and the price was more than it is usually but not the astronomical ripoff that come places can be. Tony was very easy to deal with, everything was as described  and he was a text away if anything was needed. The place also looks better than the photos show.  There's a big supermarket around the corner, a fantastic Mexican restaurant (Habanero) is very close and there's loads of stuff within very safe walking distance.  Don't be fooled by the name, this is no monstrosity.

I loved staying here. It was clean and cozy, very comfortable bed with nice soft sheets. Towels were laid out for us, and everything worked the way it was supposed to. The apartment looked just like the pictures inside and out. I enjoyed walking through the neighborhood to Quack's for coffee both mornings, and would definitely recommend this over any hotel! Thank you!

Myself and a group of collegaues were in tow. For a conference at the Austin Convention Center.  We could not have stayed in a more convenient and affordable location as Chads apartment.  Located in a an old railroad warehouse, this modern trendy loft was plenty big for 6 of us.  The ammenities and services available in this spot were of the highest quality.  We very much enjoyed our time staying here.
Great place, great location, well furnished and worked great for our team's stay.
Great apartment and easy to check in and out of.
Very responsive, house was beautiful we were minutes away from everything downtown. we had a great time
A great experience. I would definitely stay at their location again. Very sweet people.

Booked two of the hosts properties for a downtown Austin wedding we attended. Convenient location to downtown, great restaurants and shopping nearby, and clean and "at home" feel to houses. Added bonus - hosts A+ with communicating as well with response time.

Wonderful stay with John and Vivian! The house is beautiful, the area is spectacular. We loved sitting on the balcony with them, overlooking the bird sanctuary. They were great hosts, providing us with everything we needed, including organic bath products and filtered water!

Amazing loft apartment just a block from 6th street. Neal & Melissa are great hosts, and gave super detailed and helpful information. There's a private parking garage, and a key drop box, meaning we could check in and leave with ease. One of the best AirBnb's we've stayed in, would highly recommend it!
Jason's place was great for our visit to Austin. It was very clean, spacious, comfortable and private. The location is close West Campus and is an easy walk to restaurants and shops.
Ryan was a great host. He was very helpful & responsive. Will definitely go back again!

Elizabeth was extremely easy to work with and very accommodating. She was flexible with us even though we had some uncertainty in the schedule of our trip.

Her house is also extremely cute and conveniently located close to everything you need in Austin! Plenty of room to get comfy with a group of friends. 

I would definitely recommend staying at her place if you're looking to spend some time seeing what ATX has to offer!

Mitch was at work when I arrived on a weekday, but he was able to get the key to me and had a welcome beer waiting in the fridge. The listing description was accurate, there was a private bathroom attached to the bedroom which was very convenient. When I did get a chance to meet Mitch he was very friendly, and he was willing to answer questions even when he was away.

The neighborhood was nice and felt safe, and was a short walk or Lyft/Uber to South Congress or downtown. It was also close to the highway which was nice for getting to/from the airport.
Octavia was a great host. The apartment was as described and she even provided a spare mattress to accommodate all three of us. The King size bed was very big and comfy.

If I could give this 10 stars I would! The view of the entire city alone made this stay worth it. The hosts had a detailed check step by step check in process that was very helpful.  The apartment was exceptionally clean and the location was absolutely perfect. I would recommend this place to anyone visiting Austin! We really enjoyed it.

Kevin and Bob were great hosts, I didn't have the chance to meet them in person during my brief stay but they were great about communicating everything we needed to know by phone/text. A very comfortable and fun place to stay, good central location. Highly recommended!

The house is in good condition. We had no functionality problems. Good public transportation going back and forth to SXSW. The neighborhood is not the best in Austin and I believe the price we payed is only valid because of the SXSW demand but would not consider paying the price on  another week. The owner left the house with cooked food in the fridge which we believe was not for us, and lots of their personal belongings all around, it made us feel a bit uncomfortable, but nothing that would make me not staying there again. On my next stay I would ask that all the food that is cooked like left overs should be taken out of the fridge, and personal items like jewlery, soaps and personal care items stored. On the good side: Lots of towels, nice porch and backyard and a welcome basket with goodies and most important, great internet connection!!!!

Mariana was extremely helpful throughout our stay. She asked if we needed anything more for the house and when we checked in and again a few days later.  The house was absolutely perfect. Plenty of space of our group and a nice backyard and grill to cook with. It was just a short $10-$15 cab to downtown Austin. Overall it was a fantastic trip and I would highly recommend this property to anyone visiting Austin!

Enjoyed staying at 2400 Bluebonnet Lane.  Great location and fantastic local restaurants.  Easy access to COTA.
Thanks,
Wilson & Cherie

I booked with Lindsey at the last minute for a trip to Austin but had car trouble on the way down. It was after 11 pm by the time I got to the house and unfortunately there was no key in the lock box. I contacted Lindsey and she apologized multiple times and has given me a full refund without hesistating.
Great location, close to all major attractions in downtown Austin. Clean, spacious, and had comfortable beds.

Christina was the perfect hostess! She had everything we needed to make our 4 day stay comfortable. Sweet Central Suite is charming and matched its description perfectly. We would definitely stay here again.

Lizzie & Forrest were excellent hosts! Great communication - any questions we had were answered immediately and reservation details were messaged to us promptly. The room was very comfortable, clean and well-maintained. The way the place was furnished and everything inside that was provided made us feel Home. Thank you Lizzy & Forrest for an awesome Austin experience and suggesting the very best places to visit in town !!

Our stay at Isaac's place went off without a hitch. He made himself available to answer any questions we had about the place. Well updated and roomy. Recommend staying here for sure! FYI the two beds in the garage are doubles, not queens.
Mary was a great host.  The house was clean, simple, and stylish.  We didn't have much time to explore the neighborhood near the house but drove to locations 10 minutes away that were great.

We LOVED our stay at Gary's house! Besides being very comfortable and beautifully decorated, he left out fresh cut flowers in almost every room and information on the home and how to get around Austin. I don't know the last time I have felt so relaxed- this house was the perfect getaway! We had 5 people, but could have easily had a few more. 

The location was perfect within walking distance of yoga, restaurants, coffee shops, bars, etc. I was able to run over to Lady Bird Lake from the house and take a stroll through graffiti park. 

I would recommend to stay at Gary's to anyone looking for some R&R with steps away from all the Austin attractions.

The beds were comfy and we had a wonderful time. We really appreciated the large kitchen and living space. The living room furniture is different than in the photos (and not as nice, not super clean), but it did the job. We loved the patio and the porch and it was a comfortable size for 10 girls on a bachelorette trip.

Staying at CJ's beautiful home has been a special experience for me. I've very recently relocated to Austin, Texas and I needed a quiet and restful place to stay for awhile and think. CJ and her boyfriend Nate have been so kind and have made my stay very comfortable and safe. The neighborhood couldn't be any prettier or more quiet.  The nearest neighbors are cows, horses and even Alpaca. Staying here has helped me to decide that I will relocate to Austin.

The house was perfect for our weekend getaway.  Very close to both south congress shopping and 6th Street nightlife.  I accidentally left a few things and Whitney was kind enough to leave them in the mailbox for a friend to come pick them up.
Nice house with comfortable beds. The layout was perfect for our group (3 bedrooms with a queen in each).  Kate was very easy to work with. The 6pk from a local brewery was a nice touch.

I had a wonderful first time AirBnb experience! Kate was a phenomenal host - very prompt with her responses and so thoughtful for leaving us some snacks when we got there. Check-in is so simple and the house was even nicer than described. 6 of us stayed in the house and it fit us all perfectly. This house was exactly what we wanted -- free parking, walking distance from downtown or a quick cab ride, and super clean. I would absolutely stay here again. Thank you Kate!

This house was absolutely perfect for our 5-night stay in Austin. Location cannot be beat, we literally were able to walk everywhere from here- downtown, Barton Springs, bars, restaurants, S. Congress st. So close to everything, but also tucked away in a quiet side street and very safe neighborhood. The pool and hut tub were both amazing to have in the back yard, I don't think there was a single day or evening that we did not take advantage of them. Liam and Chad are so friendly and helpful. We went to every place they suggested, and each one was better than the last! We never wanted to leave! Highly recommended!!

Great place with a lot of character.  I was busy with work and didn't interact too much  with Blair, but he was extremely nice I felt completely at home.

Thanks!!
Gordon
This was the perfect place to have our bachelorette weekend. The house is beautiful and was very clean and comfortable.  Definitely keeping this one on my "save" list.

Ben is a great host. He made us feel very welcome, allowing us to drop off our bags inside before check in time so we could walk to lunch with our son who lives in Austin. The neighborhood is residential but walking distance to down town. I was in Austin for a conference at the Convention Center and either walked, ubered or rode a bicycle to all the down town events I attended ( conference, show at Austin City Limitis and receptions).
Great place! Clean, very comfortable bed and FANTASTIC bathroom. Ben was a great host too! Took his recommendation and spent a quiet evening a coffee shop down the road. Will stay again!

Laura was a great Host available for to answer any questions, the location and accuracy of her listing also top notch,  the Neighborhood was quite and peaceful and really close to some great restaurants and bars.

Laura's house was absolutely perfect for what we needed. She was extremely responsive and supplied us with everything we needed. Her place is located about 10 minutes outside of downtown and using a ride sharing service was very convenient. We would definitely stay here again!

Fantastic stay in Austin. Great location, walking distance to SOCO and plenty of restaurants, bars, shops and live music venues. Chris was so welcoming from the beginning, going above and beyond. The cottage is exactly like it is represented in pics and extremely comfortable. Chris even had chocolate and wine awaiting us! Would highly recommend.

Chris was a great host. He was always available to answer any question we had and he had a lot of local knowledge about places to dine and shop. The house was great! It was conveniently located off of South Congress Street with loads of great restaurants within walking distance. Overall a great place to stay when in Austin!
My friend and I loved staying here. Great spot and super cozy. Excellent, swift communication made things a breeze. We will be back!
The best house ever!
Easy enough would stay again nice area :)

Cons: (1) It was dirty - the sheets had clearly not been washed (hair and other dirt throughout them); floors hadn't been swept; bathroom had hair in the sink and shower. (2) The hosts didn't live there (it seemed to be managed by a third party) so the atmosphere wasn't very nice - it felt lifeless and abandoned. (3) Limited amenities - didn't have a TV, laundry facilities or extra towels/bedding.

Pros: (1) Location was great - close to lots of food trucks, cool restaurants and bars, the interstate freeway and Downtown. (2) Bed and pillows were incredibly comfortable and the air-conditioning in the bedroom was excellent. (3) Cheap.

Summary: If you can stand the dirtiness, the very comfortable sleeping conditions and great location make it worth it.

We were a mom&dad visiting our son at UT and Pete's was a great place to stay!  The location in a pretty, quiet, walk-able neighborhood was super!  The space was immaculate and just as expected from the pictures and description.  The bed was very comfortable. Pete responded immediately to any communication we had - he seems very well organized and experienced in having guests!

To me, the place is quite near to almost every place I visited when I was in Austin (30 mins to Lake Travis & Mount Bonnell, less than 15 mins to Ladybird Lake Trail, and quite close to some of the city attractions like the Capitol, University of Texas at Austin, to name a few). I recommend this place for a few days stay in Austin.

Cat was lovely and her home was perfect for us. We visited Austin for US Grand Prix with 6 people. The located of the house was awesome (close to shops, bars and food!) and the property was adorable, with dogs and plants and a great porch and chickens. The porch and hammocks were amazing for casual relaxing, and the washer/dryer was so helpful with 6 people! Beds were great, kitchen was perfect, wifi was wonderful, shower didn't run out of hot water. We will totally stay here again! Thanks Cat!

Josh and Adam were great as were their adorable dogs! The rooms were lovely and the bed was SUPER comfortable (best nights sleep in ages). I would absolutely stay there again if I was in Austin. For sure!

Well appointed and very comfortable place. I often stay at AirBnB's when in Austin and this is simply the best. Convenient location of you blhave car or low cost taxi rides to SoCo and S. Lamar. Wipl stay again if it available

We booked Lisa's place at the last minute. She was totally accommodating and helped us get the keys in an easy fashion. Her apartment was darling and I commented to my friend that I'd love to get to know her personally just based on the cuteness of her decor. I highly recommend Lisa and her wonderful condo.
Nolan was a great host! The house was perfect for us--lots of space (in and out!) to lounge around in. Great location, easy to walk to so many restaurants!
Great place to stay! The neighborhood was quite and near some great restaurants. Betty was very accommodating. I would definitely recommend staying here. Will be back soon!

Tj was a fantastic host and her home is beautiful and very welcoming. It is by far, the cleanest Airbnb I have ever stayed at! Everything was perfect and comfy. We enjoyed our stay and had a great time walking around the neighborhood. There are a lot of great places walking distance from the house: you can walk to 11th in 2 minutes and enjoy some of the restaurants and food trucks there or you can walk all the way to 6th street in 10/15 minutes. So the location is ideal. 
Tj was really good at giving us some cool suggestions about places to eat and visit.  Next time we visit Austin, we will be staying here again.
James, was a great host! He had everything we needed when we arrived. No complaints. :)
This is a very nice house located in a great neighborhood.
Great house, perfect location.  Everything was amazing.
Jinny's place is quaint and cozy. The bed was very comfy and the she shower was perfect! I enjoyed my stay.

Sydney was a great host, super responsive and accommodating. Her place was very clean and she had obviously gone to a lot of trouble to prepare for our arrival. Clean linens and towels were waiting for us as well as  a nice note with WiFi info. The apartment is located in a very nice quite part neighborhood with easy access to downtown Austin. Never paid more than $10 for an Uber / cab home.  Would absolutely stay here again.

Sydney was an awesome and gracious communicator and very easy to work with. Her place is very conveniently located in a great area near downtown. The apartment is clean, tastefully decorated, and the bed is super comfy. I highly recommend and would definitely stay there again.
Welcoming hosts and wonderfully friendly dogs.
We enjoyed Pam's cozy home! Thank you for hosting.

The Zach Scott home was really just lovely. It was very clean and comfortable to stay in. The home is located in a cool neighborhood with awesome restaurants (Try the Salty Sow). Brooke made check in and check out very easy by providing all the information you would ever need through an iOS app. I would definitely stay in this home the next time I visit Austin.

I had a wonderful experience at the Shasta Trailer. The room was clean and nice, the bathroom was a challenge but hey that's glamping. The property and location were great as well. The fire pit in the backyard was an excellent touch. 
The service was seriously excellent. Wine glasses, help with music, even pictures to take home. Every effort was made to be accommodating and ensure quality. An excellent place to stay, highly recommended!
Clean and complex is easy to find. Bring dish soap and trash bags. Other than that, the place is great!

I had a great time staying with Anne Marie and Lauren. They were extremely helpful in letting me know how to get around Austin, and suggested some places to grab dinner. They were both very friendly, and I enjoyed getting to learn more about them and why they love Austin. The place was clean and in a good location. I travelled by myself and felt perfectly safe coming back, even late at night.

Brandon was very friendly and responsive every time I spoke to him, my  bed was comfortable and the shower was great. The overall level of cleanliness of the house can be improved. All went well, but there has been one night with music and noise till very late, but that happen just one time,Brandon apologized for that and the other nights I spent there were fine.

Denise has one of the most unique and charming apartments that I've ever visited.  The bed was clean, the art was full of energy and the location was perfect.  I didn't have a car and was able to get to where I needed to be with ease.  Live music and good food were a stone's throw away.

Listing as described; host was very good.  Checking in and checking out was a breeze.  Neighborhood was not bad, seems like it's still being developed so not a ton in the immediate area but great proximity to downtown and the most sought after parts of Austin.  Big plus for town lake access right across the street; the run / bike trail and parks near are awesome.  Only thing I'd do different is have an option for an additional key fob (makes it difficult with a group) but this may not be allowed by your complex.  Overall we had a great weekend and Kevin's spot was very nice.

T.M. was a great host and the property came as advertised.  It's nestled inside a quiet, peaceful neighborhood and the abode has a very charming and isolated backyard area.

T.M. was very responsive and courteous, and I'd love to visit again.

Great place for one person or a couple. Comfortable bed, well-equipped kitchen and Roku.  Easy walking distance to a great coffee shop, and close to lots of good restaurants and bars. Short drive to downtown. We have a great stay!

Dallas was extremely responsive and accommodating before we ever got to the house. The house was as advertised and made for a great location for our party. It's a well appointed fun space in a good location and managed by a great host. Recommend all around. Thanks!
Great place, next to a popular landmark. Sarah was awesome, and I loved her cat! Will defiantly use again if I am in Austin

Lydia made my mom and I feel welcome right away, and was in communication with us throughout our whole stay. Everything was explained in great detail, and we were left with no questions at all. The check in was extremely smooth and Lydia had a cute room and clean bathroom waiting for us! Her house was beautiful and definitely a nice stay for anyone wanting to be close to the city but still needing a peaceful getaway.  The lake access was nice, and so calming!   Lydia herself was very nice, and made us feel extremely welcome. Thank you Lydia!

We loved staying with Miyeon! It's a nice comfortable room with a private entrance which was very convenient for us to come and go. 
We arrived late and Miyeon was kind enough to stay up to let us in and show us around the house. He made us feel very welcome. We would recommend his home and hope to back again!

Our stay at Megan's duplex was wonderful. It was very comfortable and cozy. The location was also great, we were able to goto downtown within 10 minutes. I explained that our group was celebrating birthdays this weekend and she provided us a nice birthday basket. Also, provided us clean towels to use for our day trip to the lake. I would highly recommend staying at this place.

Fiona was a great host, and the little cottage is straight-up adorable. I'm still newish to this Airbnb business, so I showed up on the wrong doorstep (Fiona's home rather than the adjacent cottage), and she was more than gracious about it, walking me over to show me how to use some appliances and such. She also gave me great input on places to eat in the area. The location is fantastic, too. I headed out for a walk to one of the recommended restaurants and ended up spending the day tooling around downtown on foot. I really didn't appreciate how close this east-side spot was to everything. The state Capitol is about two miles away. The only hitch with the location is that my online maps had a little trouble finding it, and so did the cab driver who came to pick me up for the airport. I think GPS really wants to put you on the next street over, so it's something to keep in mind. Also, I stayed here solo -- totally perfect and half the price of the Sheraton would've been -- but if I'd been with someone other than my husband, the bathroom might have been too close to the bed to feel comfy. That said, the bathroom is one of the coolest-looking parts of the place. All in all, it's a perfect little spot to have your own kitchen in an interesting part of town rather than a stale hotel room. Definitely recommend.
The reservation was canceled 5 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.
Fiona's sweet sexy studio is perfect in every way!!! Clean, cozy & perfect location. We'll definitely be staying again. My boyfriend & I have deemed it "our secret bungalow"

This was a lovely place to stay while my friend and I were in Austin! Very close to many great places and there was a fairly close by grocery store and Walgreens. There were bikes which we didn't get a chance to use but I wish we did! The kitchen is small and the fridge is tiny, (no silverware or mugs either) so go out and enjoy that Austin BBQ!
It was comfortable, secluded, and relaxing.

Michael Ann was out of town when we arrived, but she gave us detailed instructions on how to access the apartment and how to treat the space. When we did finally meet her she was extremely welcoming and helpful helping us figure out what to do and where to go during our short stay. And the space is absolutely lovely! I personally enjoyed having the piano to play around with in my downtime! Overall, I don't think we could have had a better experience

We loved our stay here! Michael Ann was a great host, offering snacks & maps around town. The apartment is exactly like the pictures. It's a fantastic location, impeccably clean, and very comfortable. We look forward to staying again!

We stayed at Lisa's for a few days while we explored Austin, and the place was perfect! A working kitchen, lots of outdoor space, and close to plenty of delicious food! We put bikes together and rode all over town from her house. The place was clean and well equipped with everything we needed including a comfortable bed and deluxe shower. The art on the walls was so interesting and eclectic eith a great feel. And of course, Lisa was extremely sweet and communicative! Just another tip: If you stay here you MUST eat breakfast tacos at Veracruz on Cesar Chavez. We ate there all three mornings that we were in town!

This house is in a neat neighborhood within walking distance of several great shops and food places, and driving downtown didn't take long either. The house is very comfortable. We enjoyed the covered back porch and checking out the funky art on the walls. Lisa was very accommodating and responded quickly to messages. I'd definitely stay again, given another chance to visit Austin!

I can't say enough about how great this room was and how wonderful our hosts, Alexandra & David, were.  The bed was beyond comfortable and all the amenities, such as fridge, tea kettle, and local Austin books and magazines, made this stay unbelievable. The bathroom was very clean and spacious, which made it easy for my fiance and I to get ready simultaneously. We loved the location, and our warm hosts guided us to numerous local restaurants and attractions. We can't wait to return!

Had a chance to stay in my old neighborhood for 2 nights while at a conference. It was perfect! Alexandra was warm and helpful. The room is attractive with a great shower, and I slept like a rock on the comfy bed. Will return!
Wonderful stay! Gorgeous house, amazing bathroom, and extremely kind and gracious hosts! Can't wait to come back!

My friend and I stayed in Kristine's flat while we were in town to see a concert. The house was adorable, smartly decorated and had everything we needed. She even had a selection of beverages in the fridge. The bathroom is especially rad. The location was walking distance from bars and restaurants. We met Kristine briefly, and she was super friendly and very welcoming. I'd love to stay again next time I'm in Austin.
my best friend and I loved staying here for a weekend. it was conveniently located, just a short uber ride anywhere downtown. stayed cool even on a warm day. big, open bathroom. no real complaints!
Quite neighborhood in east Austin, 20 minute walk to the capital/downtown. 2 blocks from Austin's oldest cemetery. Host communication was top notch and easy.
So nice! Room was perfect and private! Close drive to everything we wanted to see! Absolutely would recommend this stay to anyone and would definitely stay here again

This Airstream was even better than it looked in the pictures, and the pictures look pretty damn good! It's super-clean, the mattress is very comfortable, the overall interior design is delightful. There are so many thoughtful, functional touches. I recommend it highly. 

The neighborhood is residential, cute and quiet, yet the location is close to all things in groovy South Austin. Loved it! The common area in the house is really lovely and user-friendly.; t's spare, spotless and thoroughly pimped out with designy vintage furniture and oddments. The kitchen and bathroom are great, the bed linens and towels are really nice.  Small touches abound. 

This is Airbnb at its best. Rene is generous, flexible, responsive and thoroughly accommodating. She's a 5-star gal.

We absolutely adored this airstream! We are so glad we got to stay here for a few days. It was perfect to come back to after a full day of walking and sight-seeing. Super comfy and made it feel like we were coming home instead of an Airstream. We will visit again!!

The place is exactly as described! Perfect for a staycation or simple couple nights stay.  Instructions were communicated to us ahead of time and they were super nice and helpful. 5/5 would recommend.

Condo was just as described and amazing locations. Sue was very accommodating and had everything ready to go when we got there. Great taco truck across the street, few blocks to Franklins BBQ and 5 minute walk to the heart of 6th street. Would definitely stay there again.

Thank you both for making me feel safe and at home! I really needed that because it was my first experience in the US and with staying in an Airbnb. I loved the bathroom and the comfortable bed. And I was also very happy with the use of your kitchen. I enjoyed sitting in your big garden, looking at the cat playing.
Thank you for lending me your bike. As a Dutch woman I enjoyed riding the bike in the neighborhood.

This was a perfect Airbnb experience. The guesthouse was exactly as described; I'd stay here every time I come to Austin, if possible. It's a very nice property -- a great place to relax. The hosts were very accommodating and friendly. I'd highly recommend this property to anyone. Thanks again for a great stay. Ray.
Jeffrey's place is really great if yo want to just crash for a night. It's in a pretty convenient location. It was a really stay.

We had a great time! Taylor was always quick to respond to my messages and was very welcoming! We had everything we needed, the place was very clean and in a very nice, quiet, wooded area, but just minutes from so many cool places. We will definitely stay there again if we visit Austin in the future :)
