Space was as advertised: bright, clean, well-decorated and easy to relax in.  Very quiet side street within walking distance to East-side restaurants & a B-Cycle station.  Communication was easy & helpful - Andrea answered all my first-timer questions and Roman sent a quality list of recommendations for local dining and places to check out in Austin.  All good.  A sturdy handle at the top makes ladder navigation more secure.  Netflix + digital antenna to catch the Packer game.  ;) Way better than a hotel room for 2-3x the price!

The listing description was very accurate - what the space looked like and was described as online was exactly what we experienced while staying there. We felt welcomed by Roman and Andrea in the time leading up to our stay with helpful communications and recommendations for places to go during our stay in Austin. We would love to stay there again if we return to Austin for another visit.

Stop looking for other places to stay in Austin!  Just stay here! You won't find a more beautiful place or neighborhood, I swear!

My stay was an unusual one as I live in Austin, but rented the space for a week to treat myself to a mini artist residency with an open house of sorts for people to view a performance art installation at the end.  The house was so neat and clean, and such a beautiful space to be in!  

Seriously, stay here!
As advertised. Easy check-in, clean and ready to go! Netflix died on us, but that's not on the host.
Danielle's cottage was the best home from home imaginable - we couldn't have asked for more!

Cecily is in the basement apartment in a gorgeous building. The upstairs landlord, Blair, was very nice as well. We had a large bed and a private bedroom at the end of the hall in her apartment. I found the bed to be rather hard, but I do have a sensitive back. Cecily's daughter is adorable and both of them were very welcoming. You just can't beat the location! Walking distance to tons of bars and restaurants, the Capitol, and if you don't mind a longer walk, you could get to UT Austin. All in all a great trip, great location and very nice people.
Will was always available when we had questions, really nice 2 bedroom! We had a great time at ACL :-)
Great person wonderful host...helped out on short noticed ...
Awesome spot to stay at. Julie and Kyle have a very cute, clean and convenient spot and they are very helpful hosts.

I stayed here for SxSW and had a wonderful time. Steve was the perfect host. I didn't end up spending too much time at the house as there is so much to do at SxSW but for the time that I was there - it was perfect. Hoping to stay again
Extra rooms in a residential house. Nice neighborhood. Not really walkable to central Austin or ut. Serves its function

We were extremely pleased with the accommodations of this beautiful, spacious home in SE Austin!!! Nicely appointed, perfect for family getaways and/or reunions, easy access to Austin highway corridors! Highly recommend!

Myself and 4 of my girlfriends stayed at the guest house and had a great experience! We each had a place to sleep and the house was extremely clean and lovely. It's air conditioned too which was nice since the days became hot! Steph and Joey even left us some breakfast foods and let us use a bike, and we loved seeing their dog Dozer in the yard. It was in a good location as we moved around all of the pockets of Austin. I would defintely recommend this house to anyone traveling to Austin.

Staying here with my wife and two teens while visiting Austin was our first experience with Airbnb and it'll be tough to beat. Great hosts, excellent location, and a very comfortable place. WIFI wasn't too good but we were not on a business trip so didn't matter. We had a car but there are many things within walking distance, especially the Launderette!  Excellent food!! Pluckers is a great place for wings and a brew! We would definitely consider staying here again on our next Austin visit!

Rene's response time was lighting bulb fast, which was exactly what i needed since my trip was so last minute. She called and made sure everything was ok and let me know the house was ready for me and my guests. Super nice! I wish we would have met in person. Truly Amazing! the listing description was very accurate and EVEN MORE than I EXPECTED. Coming back to the neighborhood gave me such a homey feeling, and walking in the house was even better as you are welcomed in a clean, art decorated, modern home. we loved it!

What a wonderful stay and a very lucky find!   Would recommend to anyone who wants a fresh, relaxing, clean, delightful and fun place to stay in central Austin.   The neighborhood is wonderful and peaceful and only a short walk to Barton Springs.    Lois is very welcoming and has great fun taste in art, landscape, decor, and architecture.  This is the best of Austin crystalized.

Everything was great!! We never had a chance to meet Lois in person but she happily helped us out by phone when we had a question. The space was colorful and eclectic, making our stay in Austin very interesting.
Super quirky awesome experience in a fantastic location near the park. Lois is awesome and helped introduce us to Austin's unique culture.

Paul and Julia were excellent hosts. As soon as we arrived, we were welcomed with a friendly email full of local/informative austinite tips that made sure we got to visit the best spots. The accommodations were extremely clean and perfect for two people to live comfortably. Paul and Julia's hospitality was unmatched (they invited us into their home for drinks and continued to check in with us to ensure we had the best time possible). We highly recommend this airbnb for anyone looking to have a true austinite experience!!
Very easy to find great place great host

This place was overall great. Location was stellar as well as ease of instructions on parking and getting in the facility. Surprisingly spacious loft and comfortable beds. Appreciate the suggestions for stuff to do around town. Rules may seem strict but we did not have a problem and everyone was upfront on the expectations. Would love to stay again next time in Austin.

We were there for a work event.

Location and Convenience to downtown Austin and Convention Center was great! Super easy access. 

Good for the value  and considering it accommodates four adults, each with their own bed. 

Areas of improvement: Internet very poor, only one TV in common area and the furnishings seemed a little cheap, or maybe just run down.

Great location, and very comfortable!  Clean, and good AC in the hot summer months in Austin! The host was extremely responsive and helpful during the booking process; and flexible with the check-in and check-out, giving options for both, which was much appreciated.  I would highly recommend staying here.
Great getaway! Cosy little casita, very private, great amenities, safe and close to the wildlife. We enjoyed our few days off in Austin and our stay at Megan's casita.

Great spot to stay for the fly-by-night backpackers or in our case just for a quick night's stay. Cute bungalow in a modern suburb. We were not worried about our car because the neighborhood felt very safe. Two very adorable puppies welcome you in and were very kind. Clean, cute little home.
Really nice place good location we recommend

Karen and Patrick were very good hosts.  Accommodating with check-in/check-out times as well as communication throughout our stay.  Their children are very cute and friendly and spent some time with us but Karen did let me know if we wanted to be left alone she would come get them.  The space is very cute and clean and the location is good.  If your a walker you can get to most places in the city no problem!

MUY COMFORTABLE HABITACI√ìN
AREA MUY BONITA Y TOTALMENTE LIMPIA
Great place and near two bus routes that go to the heart of downtown. Mat was eager to help any way he could.

Kerin's place was fantastic! Big, clean, and only steps away from the action on 6th St. She was a lovely host who gave clear directions and was reachable throughout my stay for any troubles. I highly recommend her loft for any travelers to Austin!

Jay's apt was exactly how it's described! Clean, comfortable, and lots of space!  Most importantly, the location was unparalleled! Quick walk to most of 6th street. South Congress Ave was just 1-2 miles away, a quick cab ride. Maybe most impressive of all was that Franklin's Barbecue was literally right around the corner! We had a great time and would recommend this to anyone.

Casita Querida was cozy and adorable--there was plenty of space and privacy with its own entrance. Janie left helpful instructions about how to control the temperature, wifi, and the bikes she kindly lent that we should have taken advantage of, as well as local restaurants and attractions. The space was clean, well-stocked with towels, blankets, etc., and we had a wonderful time! Would absolutely stay here again.
The casita was the perfect place to stay for a weekend trip to Austin! I would highly recommend it!
This is a perfect location for a great Austin experience. A great space for bigger groups that's very clean and cozy. Ideal location for anyone wanting to hit up any of the Colorado River activities!

All around very good. Caroline was very responsive, the place was quite, tidy and calm. A good place to stay if you come to Austin and need no noise around. Caroline even went the extra mile allowing us to stay extra time.

Excellent place if you're planning a group travel. Comfortable and just 5-min walk to a bus stop that lets you get to Downtown easily and quickly. 
It really is a comfortable and safe place to stay.
Ta'Loria is always helpful and kind. I recommend it a lot!
Staying at Julia's was great! The check in and check out was very convenient and her cute home is only about a 10min walk into downtown. Would definitely stay here again!

The house was in a perfect location! Very convenient walk to everywhere we wanted to be. The house is quaint but clean. It was great for what we needed which was a safe place to sleep. Communication prior to arrival was perfect as well! Thank you.

The place was perfectly sized for 2 people. Bed was comfy, couch was great, and the apple TV was an added bonus! Location was great and Alexis suggested this fabulous diner a short walk away from the apartment.  The only downside to this place is there's no on-site parking so you have to park your car along a busy street or infront of people's houses. (we, unfortuantly, got illegally towed so be careful of that)
Very convenient location. Easy check in and out. Thanks!
Simple easy convenient
The little house was amazing, romantic, and well-stocked!  A beautiful place in a great location.  We would definitely stay here again!
Great location. Right in front of all the action.  Great communication before and during our stay. I would definitely stay here again.

This place is great!  Derrick and his wife were amazing hosts and we felt comfortable/welcome.  Everything was clean and ready for us. Shopping on Soco, hanging at Zilker Park and 6th street are all 5 mins away.

Valdete is a great host. Friendly, helpful and very accommodating. The room is beautiful, really big and very clean. Had a great time staying at her place and traveling around Austin. Will definitely come back, if I were to visit Austin.

This is my favorite place I've stayed so far. It's spacious, has incredible character, and it's in a great location. Angel was quick to respond and made checking in/checking out so easy. Honestly, we wish would could have stayed longer. We came to Austin a few days early for a wedding. Had we not been with the wedding party staying in a hotel, we would have stayed in Angel's East Austin bungalow our entire stay. I highly recommend you stay here and we will definitely be back!

Angel was a delight to book with, and the house was outstanding!! Line of my housemates said "this house is one big Pinterest post!" and she wasn't kidding; it's the most adorable little house I've seen. (The "happy" camper, my room, was perfect.) Great outdoor space, and very comfy inside. (The outdoor shower is great!) So happy to stay here, looking forward to coming back!

We were 8 people, so it was very cozy in there, but if you couple-up in the 3 large beds it's totally doable!

We spent one night at AJ and Meaghan's place. They have a very nice, big house and they rent multiple rooms to Airbnb guests. The room is modern and clean. Many nightlife attractions in Austin are walking distance or a short cab ride away. Aj and Meaghan were also very helpful with many suggestions. Recommended.

Excellent location since I was at a convention at Austin Convention Center. It is a great place to stay for a quiet, relaxing evening (especially after a long day at convention).  Super clean, quiet, comfortable bed, beautiful home and great hospitality! The house rules are spot on, I decided to bring my robe because you do share a bathroom. I wasn't sure if I would like that BUT loved the room and the home setup. I absolutely love this Airbnb host, communication was excellent! Easy check in and check out!! I will definitely be back when I am in Austin. Highly recommend
The studio was superb, very clean, spacious, beautiful view and location. Additionally, Lesly was a wonderful host, very cordial and welcoming. Will definitely  stay here again.

Staying in the Eastside Bungalow was easy-peasy.  Great location and great recommendations from Jeff on the side of the fridge.  Air conditioning kept the place pretty cool too on the hottest days of the year...
Jeff included a listing of places and restaurants.  The place was fairly comfortable, although the second bedroom bed was not the most comfortable.

Sonya and Chris's place was absolutely perfect. Comfortable, clean, and cozy. I would stay here again in a heart beat. The bed was very comfortable and they had a nice selection of kind bars, coffee, beer, and sparkling waters. Easy to find and very close to downtown and a ton of great restaurants. Hope to be back in Austin soon, and I hope their studio will be available.

This house was adorable! Julia was great and met us at the house right after we arrived at the airport! It was clean, easy to find, great location, quiet and right outside of town but still only a short drive to 6th street or soco! The back porch and backyard are amazing!

Haley & Anthony's place worked out great! Very nice inside. Roomy kitchen and comfortable beds. It's also a quick ride to the shops and restaurants or an easy ride share downtown. We'd certainly stay here again.

A girlfriend and I stayed for ACL. The location was perfect for us! Walking distance to lots of food, coffee, shops. The apartment was very clean! Cozy feels... Communication was amazing!! Thanks Lorena!
Very beautiful house and amazing neighborhood! Very clean and cozy. Eric and Kimberly were very friendly and accommodating to make our stay awesome!
Great time amazing place looking forward to coming back during tubing season

Auburn made us feel welcomed and the place was everything we had expected. The location was perfect for all of the things that we wanted to visit when we were in Austin. The beds were comfortable, the place was clean and cute and had a charming decor. Auburn was accessible via text and made sure to answer any questions or requests that I had.   Couldn't have asked for better hosts!
 We would definitely recommend Auburn and Nick's property.

Awesome place! Loved the location and the bright airy feel of the studio apartment. Had all the amenities I needed plus more. My favorite part was staying behind Cenote and the juice bar where I could get fresh juice in the morning. Cory was very responsive and flexible when my plans changed a bit. Great experience!

Fantastic stay at Cody's place at Cenote Cafe! The apartment was clean, super cute and functional. The location is great - close to downtown Austin, trendy spots in East Austin and shopping in South Congress. Plus, the cafe right downstairs is perfect for morning coffee or afternoon beers. Check in/out was easily done at the cafe. Very friendly staff at the cafe as well for any questions. Can't wait to come back!
Bob was really accommodating. The bungalow was great and the location was ideal for getting to the river, east side bars and downtown.

Bob was a great host, who made me feel welcome and at home in Austin, and provided a lot of information on local restaurants/bars/coffee shops/etc. The place was clean and the fridge stocked with water and Lone Star. He even mailed me my sunglasses after I left them!

Bob was a great host! He had lots of material on the coffee table, like menus, city guides, etc.‚Äîyou know, tangible things you could physically touch and look at! That is preferable over scouring Yelp for whatever taco place might have over 4 stars. The space was super cute. I love old houses, so this was perfect. It was clean and in a really great location. Thanks Bob!

We would absolutely recommend this home to anyone traveling to Austin.  Beautiful, clean home in a nice neighborhood just a short ride to downtown ATX, parks, and an awesome dog friendly saloon up the road!
Clean room and easy walk to 6th St.

Loved this space! Perfect location to get to downtown. It was an easy 13 minute walk. Simple and super comfortable bed with a great communal living space. I will definitely try to book this place again when I am in Austin, if it is available!

This is a great home in a great location. Close to grocery stores, etc.  and to Austin, but with a feeling of being in a country setting. Paul and Krista are wonderful hosts who genuinely want you to have a great experience in their home and go the extra mile to make sure that happens! I would definitely recommend this home!

Leslie and Dylan are great hosts! We communicated easily with them during our stay at their home in East Austin. The house is clean and they were very accommodating. We liked it because there were enough beds for 4 guys to stay there without having to share a bed.

The location is great! We walked up to the figure 8 coffee shop a few times, rode bikes to town lake and Zilker park, enjoyed the barbeque at Micklethwaite's & drank beer at the King Bee lounge - all within w half-mile of the house. There is also a HEB grocery store close by for provisions & food. I highly recommend that if you are considering booking (URL HIDDEN) it!

Great home in the Hyde Park neighborhood of Austin.  Very convenient to campus, downtown, buses, and restaurants.  The house is beautiful - exactly as described.  James is a people person and very easy going.  You will feel comfortable immediately.  He will definitely be sure you feel welcomed and he checked in with us throughout the week to be sure our stay was going well.

My husband and I was lucky enough to found this place during Labor day weekend. Robin was really helpful in showing the place. The room itself is really neat, clean and very cozy with private entrance. The best thing about it is its conveniently located near a lot of restaurants and stores we wanted to visit (It's literally 5 minutes away from ramen Tatsu-ya!!!). 

We would love to come back and stay here again next time we're in Austin.
The host was very welcoming,
Yes very welcome. Great stay!

The house was a great size and had everything we needed for our weekend trip. We loved the pool and the patio as well. Rick was super helpful whenever we needed something, they even let us bring our dogs and extend the check out time.

We were greeted by host to make sure we had everything we needed. They were very welcoming...even offering extra ponchos from their own home in case of rain. The pool and patio area were awesome. I would definitely recommend this house for a group. Their were plenty of beds and bathroom space....which was great for a group of 8 girls. Thank you Rick for the great Austin hospitality!

Everything was wonderful. Stephanie and her brother are very friendly and using the kitchen whenever I needed to was simple and carefree. The bedroom (being separate from the home) is wonderfully private. I have a few more trips on the horizon bringing me to Austin. I will certainly check here first for availability.

David and his wife were extremely friendly and helpful! The house is in a great location to enjoy the nightlife on 6th Street.  The suite was clean and organized with snacks and drinks provided  If you are looking for a beautiful, quiet neighborhood that's within walking distance (or a short cab ride) of Austin's nightlife and restaurants, this is the place to stay!
Mathieu and his girlfriend were amazing hosts who provided us with comfort and insightful locals-only tips. The room/house as beautiful as the pictures ... 10/10 overall experience.

Brandon made everything very easy by providing detailed instructions and directions to the property ahead of time.  The location is unique in that it's not in the middle of the city, but is only about a 10-15 drive from most Austin neighborhoods and is tucked away in West Lake Hills near some really beautiful homes and scenery.  The property was clean, easily accessible, and spacious, and matched the description/photos.

Trey was an excellent host. He was there upon arrival, showing us everything we needed to know for the studio, as well as offering recommendations for restaurants. The studio was just as described, and perfect for our needs. Wouldn't hesitate to stay there again when visiting Austin.
Samantha was a great hostess! She was very responsive and has a cute house on the south end of Austin close to all the action.
Good place to stay. Less than 6 miles to downtown.neat and clean. Friendly people.nice patio
Cheapest room in the area and very friendly host. Would definitely stay here again.

Kim is an awesome host! Her place is super cool and inviting. The room itself is large and the bed big enough for two! When I was in the apartment, I really enjoyed talking with Kim, hearing about her life experiences and about her music, and sampling her delicious baked goods :) I'll be sure to stay there again if I'm in town!
I enjoyed staying at Kim's apartment. My bed was comfortable, everything was clean, and I was able to get in and out easily.
We had a good night in the house of Kim. The place is nice and young. We were like at home.

Zachary was always responsive and helpful with all questions regarding our stay. Perfect location for us. Conveniently near a supermarket, department store, Starbucks, really good Texas bar-b-que, Lake Travis, and in a quiet apartment complex that was easy to access from two major roads. Nicely furnished, all the essentials, great TV and streaming services, fast internet wifi. Perfect.

Adam did a great job accommodating all of our needs and was quick and easy to work with. This was our first stay with an Airbnb and we could not have had a better setup. The apartment was great and exceeded our expectations. It puts you really close to all of the adventure of S. Congress, yet was a quiet area at night. 

I'm thankful for this experience and plan to stay again in the future!
Perfect location within walking distance to everything on SoCo. Private entrance made this place great for ducking in and out at will. Would definitely consider this place again!

Laura was a great hostess! It was a real pleasure meeting her and her housemates, Thomas and Rachel. My room was comfortable and the location of her home was convenient to the spots in Austin where I wanted to be. I would go back in a heartbeat the next time I'm in Austin. 

Loved her little dog Zeus too!

Thanks Laura!!!
This was a lovely condo, exactly what I was expecting. A place to chill and unwind in the evenings.

Clean, tidy, efficient and handy. It was perfect for me to get in and out, handy to all necessary food/ highway, etc.. I was UNaware of highway's proximity--a quiet place! The sunrise over downtown was impressive also. All was within arm's reach, the need for restful surroundings was met.
Sarah's place was exactly what we needed for a quick stay in Austin. Clean and comfortable. Sarah gave us lots of info that made it easy to find.

Great, comfortable place to stay that's really close to many South Austin restaurants and cultural areas. The apartment is nicely decorated and relaxing. I'd definitely recommend staying here if you're looking for a local experience.

The co-op was a great space and the room just what we needed! It was located in a great area and great with or without a car. Jacob was laid back and fantastic, very flexible and great with communicating, he gave us tips about the area and Austin itself too. EVeryone in the house was welcoming and nice as well. Thanks for a great stay!
We really enjoyed our stay. Tracy was an excellent host!

The tiny zen cabin was wonderful! Tracy was a great host and made sure I had all the things I needed to ensure my stay in Austin was a success. The cabin is quiet and perfect for relaxation after a long day at a conference. It's close enough to walk to some restaurants. I highly recommend it.
Staying at the Tiny Zen Cabin was just what I had hoped a very quiet place to stay and very conveniently located. Tracy was an excellent hostess.
This place was perfect for an overnight stay! Very cute and great location. The host was nice and welcoming; I highly recommend staying here! :)

The room is exactly as described. It was comfortable and I felt very safe. The in-room air conditioning was greatly appreciated. I also appreciated the location and the ease of access to places to eat/drink,  as well as convenient access to downtown. Thanks for the comfortable stay Cynthia!
Staying at the Zilker Guesthouse makes you  feel like you live in Austin.  A great location with a cute house.  We really enjoyed our stay.
Great house and great hosts! Felt at home and comfortable throughout the week!
Jessica was very easy to communicate with and her place was clean and well-furnished in a quiet complex. I highly recommend it!

I was moving to Austin and needed a place to stay temporarily with a lot of space for all my stuff. This room is indeed very large, I think larger than some of the apartments I looked at while staying there. The place is reasonably quiet and easy to get to, and parking my car was never a problem at all. It's worth noting that this room is a loft over a garage, not attached to the main house, so there's quite a bit of privacy as well. Edith was always very courteous and hospitable whenever I saw her. My visit happened to overlap the Fourth of July, and Edith and Rebel invited me into their home for a barbecue meal, drinks, and conversations all through the evening with some of their family and friends. It was a very warm welcome to my new city.

The space was really close to downtown. The host was very welcoming and gave a tour. We got in and out easy. We came home really late and it was nice and quiet and safe. The neighborhood is quiet. I would definitely stay here again if I was going to Austin.

Edith's place was a great value. My friends and I realy enjoyed our stay. There are 3 beds at the top and the whole room is very spacious. You have a garage to park in. The bathroom is downstairs in the garage. Would definitely come back if I am in Austin again.

Honestly the pictures do not do this house justice. It looks beautiful in pictures but 10 times better in person! It says it sleeps 14+ but I really feel like u could sleep 20 people comfortably; the house is HUGE! It's outside the city (25 minutes or so) so it's really quiet and peaceful. Since it was in a secluded forestry area they worn you about a lot of wild life. But we saw a deer and a few wasps, but nothing major. The house comes with plenty 
of towels and seasoning which came in handy since we BBQ for July 4th. I would rent this place again in a heartbeat!

John and his fam's back bungalow was seriously perfect. Tucked away from the noise of sxsw but super close to South Congress and a short walk/uber from downtown Austin, the location couldn't be better. The space itself is the definition of comfortable and the hosts were friendly as can be. Just hope i can get it next year too!

Nathan's house is an absolute dream. It was clean, tidy, spacious and simply perfect for a relaxing weekend away. Nathan had left a ton of supplies, so we didn't have to rush to the market as soon as we arrived. The house is perfect for a family, there's a ton of room so you never feel like you're on top of one another. 

The back yard and decks are amazing. I personally spent the majority of my weekend swaying in the hammock on the front deck. 

The area is about 45mins from the airport and 30mins from downtown. The neighborhood is quiet and fairly remote (extremely peaceful). We weren't able to find access to the lake, but visited the neighborhood pool twice - which was awesome.

Location was perfect, very close to recreational trail on the river. A short beautiful walk to my conference. 
Communication was prompt and check-in and out was easy. The bed was very comfortable and the arrival ambience set a nice tone for our stay (lights low, music playing on TV and bottle of wine for winding down).
Would definitely stay there again :-)
A nice simple crash pad!

* Excellent location. It was easy to walk to the best neighborhoods. Lots of food options and nightlife close by.
* Plenty of space in and around the home. Comfy chairs, stereo, TV, and private bedrooms. Great style to the home as well.

We had an amazing staying at Sid's place. His house is very spacious and with REALLY all amenities we needed to stay a whole month and he was very solicitous with all our doubts and needs, in fact,  we just needed to buy the food. As he is not living in Austin anymore, we were greeted by his mother that is also an amazing people, she received us at the house and, as we didn't have a car, she gave us a ride to a very good grocery store, so we were able buy some goods to survive for the first days. Besides that, the place is just 10 minutes by bus from the downtown and 7-8 minutes walking to the nearest grocery store. Thanks for all Sid and I would recommend my friends to stay at your place.
Great clean space with everything as described. I really enjoyed staying here even for just one night. Thanks Dustin for making my first AirBnb experience awesome.
Good location. Easy checkin and checkout.
The house is much nicer than picture! And it was actually bigger than I expected too. It was warm, clean and artistic! You are going to love the experience in this house :)

Brian's place is very close to downtown and is easily accessible, It is in a very high end lovely community and is as clean as one could ever expect. Check in a Breeze, Check out a breeze and Communication also a breeze. I go to Austin quite often an now will always look to see if this is available. Thank you Brian for allowing me to stay at your spotless home !!! Until next time.

Amit was a great host! He went out of his way to leave some beer in the fridge for us and even stopped by to reset a circuit breaker that we accidentally tripped. The home is clean and charming. It's also in short walking distance to Rainey Street, downtown Austin, and the trails by Lady Bird Lake.
Another wonderful stay at Amit's stylish place. Everything was clean and comfortable. Amit is a great host, very responsive and hospitable.
Great place to stay for the weekend. Easy access to everything Austin has to offer. The Austin metro rail is less than a 5 min walk. Geeta and her husband were very good hosts.

I stayed here for a bachelorette party with 13 girls and it was great! Plenty of space for everyone and we enjoyed the pool. The hot tub didn't get too hot, but I'm guessing that's normal for Austin weather? The hosts graciously met us upon our arrival and even offered us a ride to the grocery store. Their communication before arrival was also great - answered all our questions promptly and even called in advance of the trip to make sure we had everything we needed before arriving. I would highly recommend staying here!
Really nice place. Cool building with so much to do. Our host was on top of it.

Great place, just like the pictures.  The house was impeccably clean and had everything you need to make your stay perfect.  It is located in a great part of Austin and very close to an HEB, a great supermarket, which made it very convenient for us.  We went to Austin for my niece's wedding and stayed for a week. Tatiana remembered this detail and left us a lovely basket with fruits and snacks with a personalized note, this was an unexpected detail and very much appreciated.  We truly felt welcomed and at home.  The house is spacious and extremely comfortable, great for the price.  I work in the hospitality industry and tend to be very picky, I have no complaints.  I look forward to returning to Austin and hopefully being able to stay in this house again.  I highly recommend it!

Host was very accommodating, even set out and aired up an extra air mattress and put a sheet on it for one of my children. Neighborhood was quiet. There were a lot of toys, books, and movies for my kids so that was an extra plus. Very cute inside. Lots of toiletries and things to cook with. Much appreciated.

This was my first time using Airbnb, and Jaclyn ensured a wonderful experience from beginning to end.  Her responses were prompt and friendly and made me feel like an old friend before I ever even stepped foot in her condo.  A group of five of us stayed at the condo for ACL weekend 1, and I could not have asked for a better location or lodging.  The condo is on 4th street, so all the action of downtown Austin and the ACL shuttle stop were just a few blocks away.  Yet, the condo faces the courtyard of the complex which keeps out any of the noise from the streets.  The condo was both clean and well-supplied; Jaclyn even left some Texas inspired drinks and snacks in the fridge for us! An added bonus that you can't see in the pictures is that there is an extra sink/mirror setup in the bedroom which really helped while getting ready to go out.  As for space, we had more than enough comfortable bedding for our five person group.  Besides the bedroom, both the couch and the recliner were comfy enough to sleep on, and there are also a few of the higher end air mattresses available.  The air mattresses had automatic pumps to inflate and deflate, and while I've slept on some lumpy air mattresses before, I honestly slept like a log while on these.  Members of our party were arriving and leaving at different times, yet Jaclyn was able to accommodate all of our needs without complaint.  She leaves you two keychains to enter the condo complex, and then the entrance to the condo has a keypad which made it very easy for our group to split up at times.  I highly recommend this place to anyone coming to Austin for a festival or looking to enjoy the downtown scene!

Erica did a wonderful job of making this such an easy and comfortable stay! There is an app and email with full instructions for check-in before you arrive. The house is a short Uber ride to all the necessities whether it's the grocery store or night-life. It's also nice to escape to a quiet neighborhood at night during the craziness of SXSW. Would definitely stay here again.
Monica was a very helpful host, enjoyed our weekend so much!
Alex's place was perfect for a weekend getaway to Austin. It's location makes it easy to get to the city. I will look to stay here on future trips, thanks again for hosting!
Lovely place with a wonderful host, very convenient to lots of great Austin destinations. Pepper and her kittens were a nice bonus, too!

John made accessing the space a breeze. The location of the property is quiet and beautiful. The space was perfect for our couple of days in Austin - it felt as if everything was a 10 minute drive away. The property is very modern yet cozy with a touch of luxury. I highly recommend staying at this location!

I am an international student at UTA and I have lived there for 6 days before school. The house is clean and tidy. The bed is soft and comfortable. I love her kitchen ! It's great to cook by myself. Also, Pauline is definitely the nicest host that I ever met! She shows me around the neighborhood to get familiar with  the transportation system and groceries. She gives me a lot of tips,which is useful for a newcomer ,and helps me a lot when I was moving to my new apartment! I like her ,and you will like her.

Six family members stayed at Tune Inn during a family wedding weekend. This was the perfect spot to hang out between activities. The backyard is an oasis, and the house itself easily accommodated all of us for meals, getting ready for events and entertaining the family with all of the musical items. The location is stellar, 15 walk to downtown, 10 minute walk to restaurants, bars and cafes in other directions. Roger is an amazing host: responsive in pre-trip communications, available while we were in the house, gave lots of good info about the area, and he keeps a super well-stocked house.

They were fantastic, as was the house. It was super comfortably, very charmingly decorated, lots of space and fun things to do, and a great atmosphere to relax. The location is absolutely perfect. I highly recommend it!

The accommodations were perfect for a very last minute trip to Austin. The house is well kept and straightforward- electric locks on each room and the front door- so it's very automated. The bed was comfortable and everything was in great shape. I appreciate the quick turn around on the hosts for the booking.
Richard's place was neat and tidy. I was there for work so mostly quiet and kept to myself but a neat area to stay in if you are looking to explore.
Priscilla was very accommodating and the place was even better than we hoped it would be.  I would recommend this place to anyone.

Great place to stay for convenience and comfort during our stay in Austin. This is my first time using Airbnb and I'm now convinced that it's a worthwhile service thanks to Frank. He was even kind enough to provide complimentary water and juice.
Great place to stay; will be back again. Brady is a great host and the accommodations are just as described with a comfortable room with desk, closet and plenty of drawers.

Matt's place was excellent--clean and welcoming and with all the amenities. Matt himself was also great--gave excellent, clear instructions, and was very accommodating when bad weather forced last-minute plan changes. I honestly wish I hadn't had so many things I had to do while I was in Texas--his place would have been really comfortable to just relax in, had I had the time.
We LOVED this little house. Perfect for a family. Tina was great!
Great location, great building

Marcos was an amazing host - I left his warm and comfortable home well rested and feeling as if I had made a friend. I was there for work, so he gave me the space and quiet that I needed to get my work done. He has definitely earned the highest rating possible - whenever I get back down to Austin, there is no doubt I will be staying there again...
Excellent place and experience! Thank you for your hospitality!

The location of the home was perfect and close enough to all areas of Austin that the group I was with wanted to see. The home itself was absolutely beautiful and very spacious for myself and the other five guests who were there for the trip. Ashley was a pleasure to communicate with and made the check in and check out simple and smooth. Would highly recommend this home to anyone traveling to Austin l.

Hugh (the landlord) is the greatest!! Welcoming us with cold beer and offering airport pickup. Hugh had arranged for brand new airmadresses and netflix on the telly. But the best thing is the area. Walk into downtown through the vibrant EAST-side is SO cool. Shoppingcenter near by (5 min walk). Will very much like to come back!

We stayed with Amy and Nick during the week of our wedding and the experience was wonderful! Amy and Nick were incredibly accommodating and helpful and so friendly. . .they even put together a beautiful flower arrangement as a congratulations! We loved the space and had no complaints. The location was perfect and the ammenities were top notch! Our little dog loved their beautiful yard and their cozy little space! We will definitely be back!

Perfect location and perfect studio. The layout and decor was great with every comfort in mind. A very thoughtfully designed space. The hosts were very accommodating and helpful. Would love to go back and stay there again!

Loved staying here! Hosts were kind and friendly and the place could not be in a better location. It's a very short walk to lots of food trucks, coffee shop, brewery, etc. Great little getaway for our stay in Austin.

This charming cottage was perfect for our stay. It was convenient to the places we wanted to go, but also felt like a cabin retreat. The interior is well stocked and decorated. The home is unique and full of character.

Adam was really friendly and helpful with recommendations for the Austin area.  The location is about 20 minutes from downtown, which we really preferred.  It is nice and quiet there with a beautiful view.  There are 3 sweet dogs on the property.  The house itself had everything we needed and was quite comfortable.
Great stay-location was good and just a quick ride downtown.

This property was amazing.  The dome itself is a truly amazing place to be able to stay if you are visiting Austin. The area the dome is in is called West Lake Hills and the name fits the area very well.  The dome seems to be almost at the top of one of these hills slightly tucked back enough to actually be out of Austin's light pollution, meaning the views from the dome are outstanding whether you are looking at downtown, the starlit sky at night, or the beautiful surrounding nature.  The area is very private and secluded, although getting to downtown or South Lamar from the dome only took 10-15 minutes at most.  Christine was amazing, providing us with beyond everything we could need as well as going out of her way to make our trip as great as it could be, which is was.  I would very highly recommend this property to anyone, whether you are visiting or even a local, staying here will make for an amazing experience!

What a great house!  It was exactly as described and had a very comfortable and homey feel to it.  Christy was such a fantastic host and very thorough in her instructions.  She also provided a super helpful how-to pamphlet, as well as, some reminders around the house.  There was plenty of parking and plenty of room in the house...especially enjoyed the deck!  The place is located just a short walk across the river to downtown and also close to a great park with a view of the city.  This place is perfect and I would definitely stay here again!  Thanks, Christy for everything!
The rental was clean and well stocked.  Brooke was really responsive to our emails.  I would absolutely recommend mellow yellow to anyone visiting Austin!

Dan & Erins garage apt is a great place to stay if you are in town for a few days (you could actually live there very comfortably :)). The room is open, very comfortable, beautifully appointed and nice and quiet if that is what you want. Dan & Erin are there if you need them but not if you don't, perfect hosts!!! My wife and I stayed for a child free Austin weekend and absolutely loved it! We will return sometime!!!

This was my first Airbnb experience. Leo & Tiffany were very welcoming and accommodating. The neighborhood was very private, and even gated at the entrance. The house was very clean and neat upon entrance.

I had a really great stay with Adam, Marla and Chloe. The room is comfortable and clean and the house is walking distance (or bike ride or bus) to downtown, in an area that feels safe and quiet. Adam and Marla were super-helpful in providing advice on places to eat nearby and things to do and were very welcoming: Adam went above and beyond his duty of care when I was late to arrive he got in contact to make sure I was OK, which was really nice and so much more personable than I would have got from a hotel. They also kindly found me a hairdryer to borrow for my stay, which was greatly appreciated! I absolutely recommend this accommodation option and would stay here again if I‚Äôm back in Austin.

I was visiting Austin from Illinois for a computer programming class called Makerprep.  The house was a short 10-15 minute drive to where I needed to go for the class downtown.  The house had everything I needed and the roommates were nice.  In the event I needed something Martin was pretty fast to respond when I needed anything.

The mansion was a real delight - so beautifully restored and we were really made to feel at home by Denise & Shannon.  We received a lovely welcome, were provided with neighbourhood restaurant recommendations, but also allowed our own privacy.  Such lovely touches, immaculate inside, and it appealed to my sense of everything in its place - there really was a place for everything!
Whilst this is a way out of the centre of austin (you need a car), we ended up using Uber for nights out into the centre which wasn't too pricey at all.
Such an original Airbnb to try if you're in Austin!

Lindsey was by far the most accommodating host my girlfriend and I have had in our experience with Airbnb.  She was very responsive and eager to accommodate our needs. The cottage was cozy and comfortable, exactly as it was described.  Overall we enjoyed our stay and hope Lindsey can host us again the next time we're in Austin.

We had a lovely 3 nights at Crow Cottage.  The Cottage is cute as a button and exactly like in photos.  Very efficient space with everything you could need for the trip.  I really enjoyed the free wifi, the little compact kitchen and of course the well needed air conditioner!!! It was Austin in summer after all.  The host Lindsey was VERY responsive and helpful.  I would recommend renting a car in Austin at least in steamy summer months, but we did manage with number 1 and 3 buses short walk from the Cottage.

Absolutely perfect for 1 person! Yvonne and Cameron's detached studio is a fantastic private spot away from the busier parts of town but close to a lot of the established AND up-and-coming restaurants/coffeeshops/bars in Austin.

Almost every amenity is available, the bathroom is clean/has good water pressure, and the bike is a godsend in Austin - less than 10 minutes to Downtown, 20-ish to Zilker, and no worries about parking your car (of course you could Uber/Lyft anywhere - Austin's pretty compact).

Can't rave about this place enough!

The most important things were spot on ‚Äì big comfortable bed with nice linens and 4 good pillows, great shower with excellent towels, and whisper-quiet A/C and ceiling fan.  Most of the time I was glad for the exceptionally quiet air unit, even though it was often not able to keep the temperature down to where the thermostat was set (low 70‚Äôs).  Another nice touch was the availability of both bright lighting and soothing mood lighting.  For us the location was perfect ‚Äì right around the corner was the ‚ÄúStay Gold‚Äù bar which was constantly having some of the best local live music around, and also the well-known (long line every day) ‚ÄúLa Barbeque‚Äù food truck.  The bike trail map and wifi were also useful.  The place was mostly clean, and I imagine that Spencer was unaware that the toilet had not been flushed and had a mold ring in it.  Drinking water was provided, although it alternated between freezing solid in the dorm-sized mini-fridge and becoming toasty warm on top of it.   Strangely the bathroom hot water ran out the one morning we got up early, but was hot again in a short 10-15 minutes.  Everything was quite comfortable, although with the living space being only about 12x20 with a single stuffed chair and no view, it was not a place to hang out.  Outside sounds were normal, and except for one short time (in 4 days) there was no sound coming from the other half of the duplex or upstairs, although on that one occasion the padding footsteps book-ended the clear sound of ‚Äúwater‚Äù streaming, with an accompanying visual I didn‚Äôt particularly need.
Awesome stay! Great location, beautiful place (exactly as shown in photos... Maybe better!), and Chet was super friendly and accommodating. Would recommend staying here.
This little lovely home was perfect for me and my gf. Peter had the place very clean and with all the things one could ask for including snacks! The description of the home was very accurate.

We didn't really know to expect when we booked this lovely home. We wanted something a little different and got way more than we expected!! Peter and Annie were tremendous hosts....mostly Annie because Peter was working much of the time! Sorry man. They were both extremely friendly and helpful with things to do in the area! My wife said she liked the thoughtful touches! Flowers, breakfast bars, magazines and water in the fridge! If you want to get the "Austin feel", this is a great place to stay! Thanks Peter and Annie. Well done!!!

Peter and Annie's place was true to its description-- a total charmer. Beautiful little back house set in a beautiful backyard garden. Clean and lovely, with thoughtful touches like good coffee and snacks. The projector and hidden pull down screen was a super cool bonus, and they had the Big Chill DVD so I was basically in heaven. Thanks ya'll!

Hip place in NW Austin up in the hills. Perfect for 1-2 people. 20 min drive to downtown. Neighborhood bars / restaurants / coffee shops a closer drive. (Republic of Sandwich for quick taco breakfast or lunch; Adelbert's for craft beer in a tap room/warehouse setting).

Crystal's accommodations were first rate as was her hospitality! We had a great time, and we were perfectly situated within Austin. We were a quick, 5 minute drive from everywhere we needed to be. I will definitely be booking with her again!

Crystal was so organized and quickly replied to my questions. Check-in was easy and the house was perfect and easily fit seven of us. Crystal was incredibly thoughtful and left us customized bar and restaurant recommendations for our girls weekend in Austin. Crystal is an excellent host and I recommend this listing to anyone looking for a great place to stay while visiting Austin.

Crystal's place is brilliantly located and has everything we could have wanted for a family visit to the city. The welcome we got and the help she provided helped us make the most out of our time in Austin. Love to go back sometime.

First airbnb experience and a wonderful one.
Space is as described and very  cozy.
Michaela was very helpful and was always prompt in responding  to any questions 
I had about the area. Worked out perfect for my commute and schedule!!
Excellent place to stay while traveling for business.

Justin was a super fun host and his little camper was super cute, and comfortable. Great location to SOCO and S. Lamar shenanigans. 

Thanks Justin!

We stayed at Alexis apartment in Austin for three nights and we were delighted.  Everything was perfect, beautiful apartment, well organized, everything clean and well prepared.  It was like coming into a first class hotel with plenty of space and all details were thought of in detail.  If we ever would own an apartment for renting out we would "copy" Alexis way of doing it.  The neighborhood was quiet and jet very well located.  Thank you again Alexis for your positive attitude and quick responses to our questions.

Catie and Kate  are the best! The room is everything you can expect for this price point. I wanted a private bath, but didn't want to pay top dollar, so I knew that wasn't going to get a master suite with a king bed, but this was everything I expected. If anything I would say that the mattress is kinda getting up there and it's not the best. But besides that: perfect place to stay!

I loved my stay in Austin.  I arrived earlier than I thought but, there were no problems  checking in. Chris had sent me instructions on how to access the apartment that everything  ran smoothly.  I was able to enjoy Austin and come to this amazing space to rest. The bed is very comfortable and cozy. The apartment is everything you see and more. The restroom is fully stocked with toilet paper, towels, shampoo, a  hair dryer, and a full lenght mirror. The couch was my favorite spot where I was able to unwind and read. There are restaurants around the corner and a Starbucks.  The bus is a few steps from the apartment that going downtown is so accessible with out a car.  I would love to come back and stay here again!

This was my first time on Airbnb and I wasn't sure what to expect.  My sister, her husband and I were all coming in from different states and needed a place to stay in town for a wedding. The apartment itself was private, beautiful, clean, spacious, comfortable and in a good walking area. What I particularly enjoyed were the small details inside the apartment such as a fold out table, small shelves near the bed to put night time stuff on, a Keurig, small fridge, hair dryer etc., plenty of hangers for clothes, snacks, extra linens/blankets etc.  It is those details that made this place especially hospitable.  I even got some sweet puppy kisses. There are quite a few things accessible within walking distance but Chris recommended Upper Crust Bakery (fantastic) and Uchiko (AMAZING) as places to eat. The street does get a bit noisy with traffic but the AC droned that all out.  I would highly recommend staying in this apartment.  What a terrific experience!

What a gorgeous and comfortable place to park it in Austin! High end everything....beds, linens and all the stuff that really counts. Even extras in the bath that you may have forgotten. Like a 5 star hotel but way more private. TV in each bedroom and BIG TV in living room. Lots of personal touches, cool artwork and your OWN private pool. 

We loved the neighborhood and particularly the easy walk to So. Congress with all the shops/restos etc. 

Bill is super responsive if you need anything but otherwise leaves you alone if you seek privacy. Perfect host. We'd stay here again in a New York minute.
I had a great stay! Madge has a very cozy, welcoming place.
Fantastic house! Great location - so easy to get to S. congress for awesome food! Easy to and from airport too. House has everything you could need in a nice quiet neighborhood.

Andy did a wonderful job communicating with us and making us feel welcome. We came to Austin for a convention nearby, and highly recommend this listing to anyone attending events at Austin Film Society or other things in this area of town. The commutes to downtown and locations in the surrounding area were simple and easy.

Vannak was a great host!  He was very responsive to questions and provided many great suggestions for what to do in the area.  The place was exactly as described and we had everything we needed and more!
The host canceled this reservation 138 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.

I definitely recommend staying here!  I was looking for something last minute and they were able to accommodate the request.  The house was extremely clean and very comfortable.  The decor was very nice and I loved the stone fireplace!  There were 3 bedrooms off the front left side of the house which shared a nice size bathroom and a very large master suite off the back with was great!  Our kids were able to play safely in the fenced-in backyard (they have a swingset) and the adults could easily keep as eye from the living room and kitchen (which was a great space to socialize!).  In the morning the sun would shine in the large living room window which was very peaceful to just sit and drink coffee while the kids watched cartoons.  The location was also perfect as it was only a few blocks from the highway which gave us quick access to downtown, the grocery,restaurants, stores and  the theater.  We plan to stay there on our next visit to Austin and recommend others to stay here as well!
Jason has an absolutely fantastic place, well placed, well situated, well stocked. Good communication too.
Great location. Short ride to downtown, shops and restaurants. Big back yard and pet friendly.

Renee's home was perfect for our stay in Austin in an ideal neighborhood. I don't think the pictures did the place justice of just how comfortable, functional and aesthetically pleasing her place was. We sat in the covered backyard and read, walked to Zilker and Barton Springs, and were able to get to downtown or South Lamar in minutes. Renee made coordinating our trip seamless and had phenomenal advice, and I hope she has availability next time we're in town!

Shins was so helpful, she have me a great list of things to do. Her apartment is so great. I felt right at home. The pool is great and the other tenants are so friendly. The apartment is right on the river and so close to downtown. This is a perfect place to stay!

After everything that could go wrong did this rainy Memorial Day weekend, Amanda and Whitney were a shining light! Their duplex is conveniently located, quiet, clean and delightfully funky! They were incredibly accommodating as my plans kept changing and I felt very welcome. Thanks again!
Such a nice neighborhood.  This was my second time staying at this apartment.  Everything is so clean and comfortable.
The host canceled this reservation 2 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.
Jake made my stay  simple and easy. The pool was a great treat and the entire place was comfortable.

We had such an amazing time at this house. Pictures can not give enough credit to have beautiful this house is. The pool was fantastic. Jake was very helpful we took his advice and went and had some of the best bbq in town.

We will come back again!

From booking Jake was friendly and informative and quick to respond.  The house is in a quiet neighborhood in North Austin but close enough to downtown that it only took us about a 10 minute drive.  Stocked better than the house I live in!  He's thought of every detail.  My kids loved the Legos and games, we all enjoyed the pool, and when it rained, the Wii was a great distraction.  Comfy beds, clean bathroom, and well stocked kitchen.  I cooked while we were there and found every kitchen gadget I needed. Great house with a fun Austin vibe that made our trip perfect!
Alison is a great host and has a lovely, comfortable home. I highly recommend.

I really enjoyed my stay at Stacia's home. I was quite busy and never actually met her during my stay but the apartment was very comfortable, just as described. The guest room is comfortable and was very clean - along with the bathroom. Also not far from downtown and the neighborhood is nice. I would stay here again!
The host canceled this reservation 14 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.

Daniel is a great host. He is accommodating, nice, and friendly. He went above and beyond by giving us a nice bottle of wine and some delicious homemade cupcakes for my girlfriend and I (it was Valentine's weekend). 

The place itself is a nice and cozy suite ("Festive Suite") attached to Daniel's house. We enjoyed complete privacy during our stay. The suit comes with anything you would want for a weekend getaway (bathroom, shower, bed, sofa, T.V., Wi-Fi, some toiletries, small refrigerator, microwave, and dishes and utensils). The place was spotless clean too.

The location is great. About a 20 minute walk from Barton Springs Pool and Zilker Park. It is a quiet and serene neighborhood. 

We also had the pleasure of enjoying some of the dogs Daniel has. Since we are both animal lovers we were thrilled, but if you do not share the same appreciation for pets do not worry -- the dogs are mostly in the backyard patio so you do not have to interact with them if you do not want to. 

Looking forward to staying at the Festive Suite again!
Daniel is a welcoming host and around if you need him.  The location is great and the place was clean.

Samantha's place was amazing for hanging out with friends that I haven't seen in a long time and exploring Austin. She gave us good tips to get around Austin and had an amazing house. Also highly recommend going to Uchi which is nearby.

Carlos is a superb host! He's friendly, prompt and more than willing to accommodate. The room is very cute and quaint. It has its own private entrance which is great for people who like to come home late. There is also a mini fridge, which he had stocked with drinks and fruit. Any concern I had, he went over and beyond to address it.  It's not terribly far from downtown either, only a $10 Uber ride. Highly recommend Carlos and his place.

While I didn't get to see Lauren during my trip, she frequently communicated with me to make sure I had everything and was comfortable. She also left me a great welcome package with instructions, snacks, and guides ‚Äì I couldn't have been happier.

The house is *really* beautiful and in a really great spot ‚Äì it's away from the street noise and only a short walk to downtown. I can't stress enough just how comfortable Lauren's home felt.

The listing is right to say that Grace, the cat, thinks the house belongs to her and that's part of her charm ‚Äì she's super cute and friendly! If only I could take her with me...

James made me feel welcomed and was very helpful, the room was very comfortable, I slept 10 hours the first night. I was in town for SXSW and it was a nice escape from the crazy crowds closer to town, I used the CapMetro rapid bus from the nearby St. Edwards stop on Congress to quickly get to and from events downtown. Enjoyed the quiet neighborhood and morning walks to Summermoon Coffee and Torchy's Tacos.

This house is stunning. It is clean and quiet and perfect. I feel spoiled after staying at Rachael's home. The level of detail and effort put into the home was wonderful. It is close enough to walk to all the hot spots yet far enough away where you don't have 6th street party-goers waking you up in the middle of the night. We will most definitely be back. Rachael thought of everything and even welcomed us with chips and salsa. I can't say enough great things about this place.
Wonderful place!  Luca was out of the country, so Dede was my host, and she was great - very hospitable and communicative.  I hope to stay here again soon.

To say that we love staying at Su-Su Studio is an understatement. We have to travel very often for work and having such a lovely place to stay each time we are in Austin makes a world of difference. It's funny, now when we check it, it feels like we are arriving at our second home. As if the wonderfully appointed studio with a killer location wasn't enough, Whitney & Erik are equally amazing. If you are looking for a place to stay in Austin, look no further!

We stayed here for my bachelorette party. The house was fine. It was a little too lived in for my personal taste. We couldn't put anything in freezer if we wanted to, fridge and freezer both were dirty, no pillow cases on pillows, dirty scissors and razor hanging in shower, half smoked cigarettes on porch.. The AC motor went out Saturday. We first reached out to Sarah who had met us in the house when arriving. She asked us very basic questions to make sure we knew what we were doing before contacting the owners. They didn't have anyone available to look at it until the following day so they did reimburse us for one night. When we would have relaxed at the house Sunday evening we couldn't because it was 82 degrees. We were having to leave doors and windows open (since it was nicer outside) which I'm sure the neighbors did not appreciate. It wasn't working again until later Sunday evening. 
The location wasn't ideal. Anything within walking distance was a good 1.5 miles. We also had uber drivers tell us not to walk around at night alone. 
We do appreciate the AC getting fixed and getting reimbursed a night without asking for it. 
They also let us check in early which was nice. For our trip and the things we were doing another area would have been more ideal.

Duane was very welcoming and provided a great place to stay. He was not able to meet us when we first arrived, but had Maya greet us and help us get settled in. The location was perfect as was the apartment. I enjoyed having a kitchen and a private place to call my own. The pools and gym were relaxing as well. I would gladly book Duane's place again and recommend it to anyone wanting a nice quiet place to stay in Austin and it's also only about a 15 min drive from downtown.

Maya met with us to show us where to park and how to get into the apartment.  She was super nice and gave us a few tips for our stay.  Parking is in a garage and easily accessible ... plenty of parking, no stress and then a very short walk into the apartment.  The apartment is nicely decorated and super clean.  There were two of us and it was a great size for us.  The kitchen wasn't pictured in the listing, so that was a nice surprise for us (we knew it was there, but seeing it added to the value of the stay!)  In the fridge is a water pitcher filter which is a nice touch.  You won't be disappointed staying here!  Duane and Maya are super and communication is easy via text once you pay.  Next time I'm in the Austin area I know where to stay :)
Great location! We asked to extend our stay by an additional night (hence two sequential reviews) and our host was quick to accommodate.

This charming little apartment was a good location for SXSW. It's about a 10 minute walk to most sessions and restaurants. Andi was a great hostess and left us with fresh towels, snacks and a list of restaurants in the area to go to. The restaurant below the apartment is quite loud though so if you're a homebody, this may not be the place for you. The beds were quite comfortable!!

Alexandria's apartment is super charming. She made us feel welcome by leaving the a/c on for us, providing us linens, and giving us great neighborhood recommendations. Apart from the charming-ness of the apartment, the best part is the location -- right in the middle of everything happening on 6th street.

My stay at Julia's was peaceful, convenient and comfortable. Room 4 has a very comfortable bed, and since its in the back of the house, it enjoys extra privacy and quiet. The house is kept very clean.  Location is great, ample parking on street and, lots of restaurants within walking distance. I would be happy to stay here again.

Great place. Big open house with a big back yard. Wifi and cable. Had everything we needed. Host communicated very well and made us feel at home. Would recommend for other groups! 

Had one slight problem with the fridge. Smelled bad when we first arrived and wasn't freezing. We realized the ice had froze the compressor up. We got it fixed and was no biggie!

We were only able to have a quick stay at this homey condo by the lake but when we arrived, we were greeted by two fawns off the back patio! Sam obliged my family and I by helping us over the phone when we were in need and was very kind.
Home is excellent, has a great lay out for a group. Host is great to deal with and attentive.
Joel was a good host, great recommendations and helpful. Place was clean and as described. Bring your own toiletries.

Elizabeth and David were absolutely incredible hosts!! We had a long driving day from Big Bend National Park to Austin and got out of the park much later than we meant to, and upon finding out we'd be getting into Austin around dinner time Elizabeth offered to make us dinner! After two days of camping and a long driving day, I can't describe how grateful we were to be offered hot, home-cooked food. We had an amazing meal with her and David and it was a real treat getting to know them. They were both incredibly nice, friendly, accommodating and our room was fully stocked with amenities and very comfortable. I wish we'd had more time to stay with them. If you're in the Austin area, don't pass them up!! We sincerely hope to visit them again!
We loved this little guest house! The place was spotless, and just what we were looking for. Jeany made everything very easy, and she was a fantastic host. Would definitely stay here again.

The host is very welcoming and nice. The house is nice and quiet, with a great view of the University of Texas golf course. The house is exactly as described, the host even became our guide, telling us where is good to visit and eat in Austin. I highly recommend staying here when visiting Austin.

Kathleen has thought of every detail of how to make a small studio apartment have every feature that you would want.  Well appointed, well stocked kitchen & bathroom.  Comfortable bed.  Convenient central location w/ quick access to trendy Austin locales.

Kathleen was an excellent host. I wasn't sure what to expect as a first time Airbnb user, but she made me feel welcome. The apartment was exactly as described and even better. The apartment was very clean, and the neighborhood the apartment was located in was very nice as well. Highly recommended!
The place was wonderful and Susan was a great host. Would stay again.

Could not rate our experience higher. Ricardo's home was delightful well appointed and comfortable. We stayed for almost a week with no car and literally walked everywhere (depends on how much you like walking as to whether this works for you) otherwise the bus system in Austin is great. The house is exactly where you want to be in terms of food, music and culture.
We felt incredibly safe in this neighbourhood walking all hours of the day and night. Ricardo himself was away, however he was brilliant to deal with and seemed a charming man :) 
10/10

Ricardo was great in prepping my space for the stay! Promptly replied to my messages, and left me with all the essential info needed. The house is small, but quaint. So glad I booked a stay near South Congress.

To our host: Thank you thank you thank you for being such a gracious and bad ass host. The place was immaculate, the keurig was a nice touch, and it was lovely to get to know you. You are warm and and did a graceful job of engaging us and also giving us space. We felt so comfortable and safe sharing your space. We will and already have recommended your place to other people in our community.

Emily was a great hostess!  She was very accommodating and available to any questioned we had. The apartment was great as well, especially the location. It's right between South Lamar and South Congress, so there are tons of great eateries close by and downtown is a short quick drive across the river. I would definitely stay here again!

Jack's house was adorable and in a great spot in town. It was very peaceful to stay in. There was cute details in the house & my boyfriend and I loved everything about the house. We'd definitely stay here again!

This place fit our needs perfectly for our weekend stay in Austin. The house was exactly as described, very nice and clean, and in a conveinent location. 5 minute drive/uber ride to downtown. Would stay again on next visit!

Dallas is the epitome of Superhost: communicative, attentive, and caring. And his place is pretty sweet, too. :)

When my friend's wedding venue was in jeopardy, Dallas asked how he could help. He even offered to take my friends and I on a tour; we didn't go only because our time in Austin was so short this visit. He also left us some local brew for our arrival, which, after a long day of flight delays after all the issues with the temporary tower at ABIA, was really appreciated.

I would absolutely stay here again, as would my 5 friends who stayed with me. We were awed by the beautiful remodel of this home and had a really comfortable stay. We enjoyed catching up on the back porch and how easy it was to walk to so much SoCo (I can say that, right?) has to offer, and a short cab ride to everywhere else. 

Thanks again for everything, Dallas!
Private, quiet, well located, and comfortable. Was easy to rest well after several long days at a technology conference.
Very clean and a great location!  Everything was as described and the check in was simple with coded door lock.
Lauren and Julie's place was great! Easy to find and gain access, quiet, comfortable; just what I needed!

Jim was actually not there when we stayed and we were sad to not meet him! He called 2 days before our arrival and made sure we knew how to get there and let us know that if there was anything we needed we could keep in contact with him. His place was GREAT for the two of us! quite, peaceful, awesome outside private shower! close to downtown and everything just a great location. Place was clean and comfy! also left some great treats for us in the fridge! We ran into a small problem but Jim made sure we were taken care of! Great Host, Cute place!
lovely place, top food vans, good vibe. Def recommend.

Jenny's place is well located and immaculate. The two bedrooms and bathroom are on a separate floor to the living area, with plenty of space and privacy. Within walking distance to local shops, restaurants, bars and a cinema, it is also in a quiet neighborhood. An excellent host providing a comfortable, friendly and professional experience, Jenny was thoughtful and accommodating with clear, helpful and prompt communication. Highly recommended.

Adam's place is conveniently located on the corners of 6th Street and N Lamar, right across from whole foods. Most of downtown was easily accessible. I was able to jog to Zilker Park and the Bat Festival without any issues. Uber and Lyft will take you anywhere from here for only a few dollars. I felt like it was a safe area. The are a couple of downsides that didn't really bother me, it's located right behind a few dumpsters from the 24 hour diner, and there's a lot of road noise in this location. For the price though, and what I was using the place for (just to sleep and as an office) it was fine. I don't you'll find a better proximity to downtown for this price.

Another solid visit to Austin, thanks to Adam! This is probably my fifth time staying at Adam's place. If you're looking for a spacious location in a great part of Austin, look no further. The fact that I keep coming back should be review enough!
Clean and comfortable. Communicating with Michaela was always quick and easy.
One of the best places you can stay in Austin
Annie was very accommodating.  Everything went exactly as communicated.  The house was very nice.  The whole experience was very positive.

Our host made us feel very welcome in her beautiful home. The room was simply designed and comfortable with the included en-suite bath.  
This was the perfect location for us, as we were attending a function in this neighborhood on the Lake.

I loved my stay at Jim O's "farmette". I stayed in the Tiny Tiny House which was perfect for my stay while I was at Austin's Psych Fest (a music festival). Jim gave me a tour of the property when I arrived, and made me feel welcome. I loved the goats and chickens, the garden and the fact that they collected rain water and gray water to use to water plants and flush toilets. Really awesome! The property was lush and green in May when I visited. The linens freshly cleaned. The composting toilet was surprisingly odor free - unlike the latrines I've used at most campsites. The outdoor shower was hot and felt adventurous. I am an avid camper so this was like deluxe camping to me - a step above actually since I had air conditioning, a comfortable bed and electricity in the Tiny house. I wouldn't recommend it to 2 people, you'd never be able to sleep 2 in the bed, nevertheless it was perfect for one!. I am 5'4 and I was able to stand up comfortably in the house, but maybe those 6 ft or more may have to stoop. There was also and outdoor shared kitchen & fridge which came in handy for storing food and drinks. I didn't cook other than toast bread, but the fact that I could have was a plus.  The next stay I will rent a car, rather than rely on taxis, Lyft and Uber. Only because I think it may have been less expensive (always watching my budget). There are places within a 10-20 min walking distance for groceries, CVS, liquor store and a Lowes. I took advantage of those. 
Overall I loved the atmosphere and the people living on the farmette were friendly and warm. Was just what I was looking for in my stay in Austin! I'll definitely be back when I stay in Austin again!
Wonderful first Airbnb stay. It's very convenient and there are various additional amenities to give you the best of being at home and at a hotel. Thanks Chet for maintaining such a nice place.

Hali and her husband Daniele are such an awesome couple and the friendliest hosts, making sure we felt right at home at all times! We arrived in the evening when it was already dark; but we had no problems finding their place, and we received a very warm welcome from Hali. Daniele was in the kitchen whipping up some gelato for dessert and kindly offered it to my son, my mom, and me. So delicious! After a great conversation with the couple, we needed to head out for dinner. Daniele told us to feel free to use the kitchen and help ourselves to any food/drink. Hali gave us some great recommendations of nearby restaurants. We ended up at Lucy's on the lake just down the road, which was a perfect spot for us for a quick and delicious meal right by the water. Hali had our bedrooms ready and we settled right in that night. It was neat to see her paintings and artwork around the house. The patio attached to her art studio had an amazing view and it was so nice to step out for some fresh air and feel the peaceful surroundings. We only stayed the night over, but would have loved to stay longer. Hali even suggested a perfect wedding venue for me to check out since she knew I was looking to get married in the Austin/Lake Travis area. Their two dogs are adorable and we enjoyed them as well. Overall, we were lucky to find this lovely home with such warm hosts! Thanks for letting us stay Hali and Daniele!
Superb location in downtown Austin. Very smooth experience. Erik & Crystal were extremely helpful arranging an early check-in and providing us with parking. Highly recommended.

Hope was gracious in accepting a very last minute request. The space was comfortable and just as described. I did not have the opportunity to meet Hope during my stay, however, she stayed in contact to make sure everything was going well. The only issue I found was that the ceiling fan is out of balance and was squeaking and clicking loudly, I had to turn it off in order to sleep.  Other than that everything was great.
Beautiful place, quiet and convenient location, and Katie was a superb host.  Katie also provided a great list of area restaurants and other amenities.  I'll definitely stay any time I'm in Austin.
The reservation was canceled 2 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.
Sam is a great host, offering lots of ideas on what to do in Austin - Barton Springs a must! The airstream is very comfortable and clean, and Sam has everything you need covered. Highly recommend.

Susan and David were amazing hosts. They accomodated our late night arrival and were super easy going about everything - especially sharing their porch/rooftop terrace with us so we could continue to hang out a bit longer. We only stayed one night and left in the morning, but we would have happily stayed longer if we had had the time. we'll look forward to
