visiting again next time we're in need of a little retreat. Hector the dog was adorable and cuddly, the coffee, orange juice, and fresh fresh baked bread was delicious, and Susan and David were warm and welcoming. Another thing worth mentioning is that their house and everything in it is truly a work of art.  I enjoyed just walking around and looking at all the little details. You can tell that a lot of love and hard work went into it. As fellow Airbnb hosts and artists ourselves, this experience was super inspiring!

We loved everything about our stay in Austin.  The backyard cottage was absolutely perfect for us, and Steve had everything we might need and more (coffee, granola, fruit, soap, bug spray, even a spare umbrella).  Steve was the perfect host, so kind and hospitable.  Always quick to respond to any questions, and had a great variety of suggestions of neighborhood hot spots.  We would 100% recommend this place and would love to visit again.  Thanks Steve!

Like others before us have said, both Steve and his wonderful backyard cottage were a pleasure. The space is exactly as advertised and Steve was both communicative and helpful throughout the entire process. If you're one or two people looking for an affordable and pleasant get-a-way in Austin, Steve is the way to go. Can't recommend this place enough!

A clean, welcoming and comfortable space to stay in while visiting Austin.  Luke and Rachel were super-communicative, made sure I was comfy and had everything I needed for my stay. I would most certainly book a stay with them again....

It was our first time using airbnb and it was great! Luke and Rachel were very accomodating. The kitties were an added plus! We had a short stay but enjoyed it very much especially being so close to everything.
Everything was exactly as described, and it was jsut what I needed. Regina was polite, timely, professional. Will be staying with her again in the future.

Jason was helpful and easy. The spot is great with a private patio in a quiet up and coming neighborhood of Austin. Do not expect any easy walk to downtown or restaurants/ bars. Very quaint and kitschy.
We really enjoyed staying!! Very clean and simple.

Susan's place was just as stated and very new, clean and comfy! The decor is nice, and the bed was extremely comfortable!! A parking spot was available very close by along with a pool. Puppy Kylie was thrilled to have guests too and very playful. Thanks for a relaxing place to lay our heads!

Faisal was a great host, and his house is in a very nice neighborhood which is close to downtown.  The rental unit is over the detached garage, so you feel like you have your own space and privacy.  Despite the hot weather, the AC kicked out plenty of cool air to make the room comfortable.  We would happily stay with Faisal again.

Ryan was very responsive to our every need when we stayed there! My group was visiting to spend the Thanksgiving holiday there, and Ryan provided us with every item we needed to make our day special.  

Also, the place looked exactly like it does in the pictures. It was very clean and spacious. (Plus the couch is awesome!)

The location is incredible - very close to 6th street.

I loved staying here. Steve welcomed me even though I checked in quite late in the day. He followed up the next day to make sure everything was ok. The space was clean, functional, and thoughtfully arranged.  I loved the windows and the wonderful play of light- sun and moon dancing upon the space.  The location rocks. The only thing missing from my stay was more time...

We enjoyed our stay at Marcella's place. The house was easy to find, and in a safe, residential area. Not as close to downtown as we would have liked, but we knew that going in. Very convenient to the freeway. It was rainy and cold most of the time we were there, so the path to the house was quite muddy. The chickens in the yard were fun, but the rooster did call out many times during the night, waking us up. The damp weather also highlighted the fact that the house doesn't have much ventilation. If we had been there when it was warm and sunny, I'm sure it would have been different. Marcella & her family are lovely, and I loved getting to know the sweet kitty :)

Beverly's place was cozy and definitely a place you could relax from Austin's bustling music and Bar scene. Also close enough to go back for more once you've recharged. Beverly herself was as accommodating as she could be she put snacks out for breakfast and even had plenty of advice for what to do and where to go in Austin. Quite honestly my girlfriend and I were amazed at how welcoming her and her dog Hank were to us. We will definitely be staying again.

The loft was very clean and full of natural sunlight, the cow hide rug and beautiful wooden furniture added to the awesome vibe this loft brings. Not to mention it was stocked with really cool music DVDs (doug sahm, blind faith!) and a beautiful upright piano which is also clean, well kept and in tune!!! will definitely consider staying here again my next time in Austin.

This was our second stay with Kathleen.  Kathleen was there to greet us and make us feel welcome again. I felt like her place is our second home!  It is so comfortable, clean, nicely decorated and quiet.  As before, we appreciated all of the extras in the fridge as well as the coffee and snacks.  The kitchen is equipped like home with all of the necessities for cooking.  We were super happy with the new 50" Sony 4K UHD TV with the (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) fiber in the living room. The other TV was moved to the master bedroom which pleased my husband greatly!  The king sized bed is comfy and my daughter enjoyed her beautiful bedroom with the two twin beds.  We love the quiet and safe Travis Heights neighborhood and appreciate the no key entrance system. As I have stated in a previous review, Kathleen could run the boot camp for other owners on how to set up and run a unit.  Kathleen's place is perfect for us.  I hope it is available for our next visit to Austin.  We love it!

We had a great stay at Jaime & Aja's place during our New Years trip to Austin. The space was exactly as pictured, well decorated, and with plenty of space. The bed was super comfortable. There was some street noise, but not enough to bother us - and there's a white noise machine which helped at night. The apartment is in East Austin, so there are plenty of great restaurants, coffee shops, shops, and bars within walking distance. And downtown is only a 20 minute walk away. Jaime & Aja were fantastic hosts and very helpful & responsive.
This is a really nice home in a great part of Austin. There are several nice Austin place to check out and some within walking distance.

Michael was a wonderful host. Although we did not meet him in person, he was very responsive and his place was exactly as described. He also left lots of little extras like snacks, toothbrushes if needed and a great guide book on places to hit in Austin. The bed was very comfortable and the condo surprisingly quite given its stellar location in the heart of Austin. We could walk to everything we needed. I also appreciated that the condo door was a code entry so we never had to worry about keys. The full washer and dryer came in handy when we got caught in the rain. This was a great stay.  Michael clearly knows how to take care of his guests.

Accurate pictures/description and a very quiet neighborhood over the weekend my husband and I were there. Perfect landing spot for our Austin weekend. If you stay here you MUST try Tiff's Treats for a warm cookie!

I had family over for a wedding and they had a great time. The space was great and Courtney was very, very friendly and easy to get in touch with. The location is also very central and close to anything you would need. I would highly recommend staying here!

Cari was a fantastic host with an incredible property. The space was ideally located in a fantastic area -- just a few minutes walk to South Congress shops and restaurants. Her apartment was clean, comfortable and quiet. Plus, she went above and beyond stocking the kitchen with essentials for the stay. She was incredibly responsive to questions before, during and after my stay, I would definitely stay at this unit again.

I'm about to shoot myself in the foot, but it's the right thing to do. This place is magical, and Bill and Melissa are among the kindest, most interesting people I've ever met. I wish I could say otherwise, so their place would be more likely to be available next time I'm headed to Austin, but there you have it. The apartment is very comfortable, open and bright, surrounded by singing birds and swaying trees. A big terrace is perfect for taking some sun or star-gazing. The property is like a lovingly tended botanical garden. Bill and Melissa treat you like a lifelong friend who's finally come to visit‚Äîwhile respecting your privacy as well. And lastly, although their property is in a lovely pocket of nature, they're within a mile of several major freeways, so getting into town or the airport is a breeze. I will never go to Austin without first checking to see if this place is available. My wife and I were very sorry to leave.

The upstairs rooms were exactly as pictured and very nice.  The downstairs rooms seemed even bigger and more beautiful than in the pictures.  This was a perfect location and a very large house with plenty of space for visiting together.  We never got a chance to even open up the pool table.  I hope we get to come back sometime.  

This house would be perfect for a big Thanksgiving Dinner!  It made me wish we were staying longer.  If you have a large family or big group of friends don't hesitate to stay here!  Wonderful!
Simply stunning. The most beautiful AirBNB I've ever stayed at, in the best location in Austin, with warm and hospitable hosts. I would gladly stay here again and again and again.

Location is perfect!! If you're looking for a conveniently located and affordably priced loft for you and your friends, book this loft with Top Trip Rentals! Chereen, our host, was very accommodating as issues popped up. The loft is a tad smaller than what I had expected; but still plenty of room for a group of 5 guys.

The place was comfortable, airy, and entirely true to the pictures. Drew was a very nice, accommodating host who offered great suggestions of things to check out in Austin. The Hyde Park neighborhood was great: quiet and residential yet sprinkled with "Austin Weird", and with a public pool and nice cafes and restaurants in walking distance. Easy access to the highway for checking out the rest of the city and nearby nature. Only one regret: I was looking forward to meeting the chickens pictured in the AirBnb profile, but it seems they no longer live at the Hyde Park Flat ;-)

It was late and dark and I had no navigation since I was on foot, so Drew guided me in on the cell phone. very nice. Roomy apartment in a beautiful neighbourhood with kitchen I did not use but everything to cook and bake was there. Drew explained me the basics of the apartment and then we discussed 10 different social economic aspects in 30 minutes. :-) Good bed, good sheets, good shower, good wifi. A short walk to the busstop which takes you to downtown in 20 minutes every half hour.  Since the apartment is a separate building its very quiet. I was there in November and it was actually quite chilly, also inside. Drew mentioned it was possible to heat but I did not bother. All in all a very good airbnb experience, an excellent, super fast responding host and a very good stay. Thanks Drew.

The hosts reached out upon booking and graciously offered tips on what to do in Austin. I took them up on it and they were very helpful. The listing was very accurate. The location is perfect--about a mile walk or less from most of what one is likely visiting Austin for with lots of very cool restaurants much closer. The apartment/building is new and clean and cool and everything works, nothing is broken or missing, its comfortable, roomy, quiet! We loved it and had a great time!

Alex was an awesome host.  He was able to accommodate me at the last minute when my original booking fell through.  

His house was great!  Clean and comfortable.  The bed was perfect.

I would recommend Alex' extra room to anyone and would love to stay again.

It was a comfortable place to stay, but very far away from the happening stuff and at times it can be difficult to leave the premise without spending a wad of cash. A great location if you arrive in your own car 


Nice place to sit back and relax! 

One thing, I believe I was staying in her daughter's room, which made me a bit uncomfortable. 


Aside from that Melita is a friendly host and very communicative!

This lovely condo was just what I was looking for during my business trip to Austin. It was very close to downtown but not too close and allowed me to get away each evening for some quiet time. Everything was brand new, the unit was clean and tastefully decorated. David met me on time and was very friendly and accommodating. He even told me where to get the best Tex Mex food and veggie fare. I will definitely return whenever I travel to Austin.

David's Austin condo provided the perfect location for our Labor Day vacation. We felt like locals with his clean and cozy place as our temporary home. Over the course of the weekend we attended a UT game, spent time on South Congress, and ventured to a couple favorite spots - Uchiko, Quack's Bakery, and Whip In. We didn't have to drive far at all to get to any of those places. We really enjoyed spending time on his back patio in between activities. David greeted us upon arrival and was quite kind. Highly recommended.
The house was just as described:  new, clean, perfect condition.   Gisela was very responsive and super hospitable.   Great location and would definitely stay again.

We loved every moment at Carol's beautiful home. The location was ideal-close to everything. The house is cozy and welcoming, with every convenience we could need. Manny was easy to take care of and we were rewarded with lots of cuddles on the couch. We will definitely stay here again anytime we're in Austin.

Tracey and James are great, generous, friendly hosts! They have a lovely, comfortable home--it's clean, spacious, and in a fantastic, beautiful neighborhood near a lot of amazing foods. And I have to mention their dog, Spot--he's super sweet! I'd definitely love to stay here again.

It was an unbelievably fantastic experience staying with Mel and Nicole. They are extremely nice people who made me feel at home as soon as I got there. 
They made my stay at Austin more memorable than I could have ever imagined.

The location was wonderful - can walk to all the shopping, bars, and restaurants on South Congress like Torchy's Tacos and C-Boys.

Ramona had everything ready! a great communicator as well. No hiccups. A list of things to do in the area, fresh eggs, were provided. 

The house is "rustic" as it is an older home. The chickens in back are fun. We even named a few of them. Parking was a breeze, right in front of the house. The house was very clean as well and stocked with essentials.

One of my best experiences on AirBNB ever. Josh was super friendly and nice. Seems like a great guy, he offered drinks, food. The room is exactly as advertised, many amenities, great looking place. I greatly recommend it.
Wonderful stay over Presidents Day w/e - beautiful scenery, quiet location but very convenient to downtown, Zilker Park, etc.  Discover the trails!!! VERY family friendly.

Zach is a very respectful, communicative and accommodating host. The stay had no faults. Beyond that Zach is a very intelligent and rational person personally and I made a new friend with this stay. 

The property is great. Large and has high-end finishes within, (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) Fiber (very fast and great channel selection) and a massive back-yard for fun and any pets. My pup loved it. 

Would stay again and recommend for anyone. Centrally located in a residential neighborhood with many options for food/entertainment around and proximal to public transport and downtown.
Lovely apartment ! So cute ! Location great !
